hment trial of Donald Trump|impeachment trial]] of the [[President of the United States]], [[Donald Trump]], begins in the [[United States Senate|U.S. Senate]].<ref name=\"NPR impeachment\">[https://www.npr.org/2020/02/05/801429948/not-guilty-trump-acquitted-on-2-articles-of-impeachment-as-historic-trial-closes 'Not Guilty': Trump Acquitted On 2 Articles Of Impeachment As Historic Trial Closes] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206152432/https://www.npr.org/2020/02/05/801429948/not-guilty-trump-acquitted-on-2-articles-of-impeachment-as-historic-trial-closes |date=February 6, 2020 }} by Philip Ewing, [[NPR]], February 5, 20204:33 PM ET</ref>\n* [[January 18]] \u2013 [[Yemeni Civil War (2015\u2013present)|Yemeni Civil War]]: 111 Yemeni soldiers and five civilians are killed in a [[2020 Ma'rib attack|drone and missile attack]] on a [[military camp]] near [[Ma'rib]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51166943|title=Yemen war: Death toll in attack on military base rises to 111|date=January 20, 2020|access-date=January 20, 2020|publisher=BBC News|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200121084708/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51166943|archive-date=January 21, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[January 28]] \u2013 [[President of the United States]] [[Donald Trump]] and Prime Minister of [[Israel]] [[Benjamin Netanyahu]] announce the [[Trump peace plan]].\n* [[January 29]] \u2013 U.S. President Donald Trump signs the [[United States\u2013Mexico\u2013Canada Agreement]], the North American trade agreement replacing [[NAFTA]].<ref>{{cite web|website=BBC News|title=Trump signs US Mexico Canada Agreement|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-51300625|date=Jan 29, 2020|access-date=January 31, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130151434/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-51300625|archive-date=January 30, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[January 30]] \u2013 [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]: The [[