 [[Donald Trump]], on articles of impeachment.<ref name=\"NPR impeachment\"/>\n* [[February 11]] \u2013 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic: The [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) names the disease [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-china-51466362|title=Coronavirus disease named Covid-19|website=BBC|accessdate=February 11, 2020|date=February 11, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200211155539/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-china-51466362|archive-date=February 11, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/world/wuhan-virus-coronavirus-who-new-name-12424116|title=Novel coronavirus to be called COVID-19, says WHO|website=CNA|accessdate=February 11, 2020|date=February 11, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200211193937/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/world/wuhan-virus-coronavirus-who-new-name-12424116|archive-date=February 11, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[February 13]] \u2013 [[NASA]] publishes a detailed study of [[486958 Arrokoth|Arrokoth]], the most distant body ever explored by a spacecraft, which ''[[New Horizons]]'' passed by on its journey through the [[Kuiper belt]].<ref>{{cite web |title='Not just a space potato': Nasa unveils 'astonishing' details of most distant object ever visited |url=https://www.theguardian.com/science/2020/feb/13/not-just-a-space-potato-nasa-unveils-astonishing-details-of-most-distant-object-ever-visited-arrokoth |date=February 13, 2020 |work=The Guardian |accessdate=February 13, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200213192141/https://www.theguardian.com/science/2020/feb/13/not-just-a-space-potato-nasa-unveils-astonishing-details-of-most-distant-object-ever-visited-arrokoth |archive-date=February 13, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=The Most Distant World We've Ever Explored Just Shed Light on How Planets Are Born |url=https://www.sciencealert.com/here-s-what-arrokoth-can-tell-us-about-how-baby-planets-are-born |date=February 13, 2020 |work=Science Alert |accessdate=February 13, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200213200224/https://www.sciencealert.com/here-s-what-arrokoth-can-tell-us-about-how-baby-planets-are-born |archive-date=February 13, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=The solar nebula origin of (486958) Arrokoth, a primordial contact binary in the Kuiper Belt |url=https://science.sciencemag.org/content/early/2020/02/12/science.aay6620 |date=13 February 2020 |work=Science |accessdate=13 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200214034203/https://science.sciencemag.org/content/early/2020/02/12/science.aay6620 |archive-date=February 14, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* [[February 27]] \u2013 [[2020 stock market crash]]: The [[Dow Jones Industrial Average]] (DJIA) plunges by 1,190.95 points, or 4.4%, to close at 25,766.64, its largest one-day points decline at the time. This follows several days of large falls, marking the worst week for the index since [[Financial crisis of 2007\u201308|2008]], triggered by fears of the spreading [[socio-economic impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|COVID-19 coronavirus]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Dow plunges 1,100 points as the coronavirus sends the market tumbling into correction territory|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/02/26/dow-futures-fall-after-microsoft-issues-coronavirus-warning.html|publisher=CNBC|date=February 27, 2020|accessdate=February 27, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226233042/https://www.cnbc.com/2020/02/26/dow-futures-fall-after-microsoft-issues-coronavirus-warning.html|archive-date=February 26, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[February 28]] \u2013 Ambassadors of all 29 [[NATO]] Allies meet in the [[North Atlantic Council]] expressing solidarity with [[Turkey]] after 33 Turkish soldiers were killed in an [[2020 Balyun airstrikes|airstrike]] by pro-Syrian government forces during the ongoing [