wo days later, the quarantine is [[2020 Italy coronavirus lockdown|expanded]] to cover the entire country.\n* [[March 9]] \u2013 [[2020 stock market crash#Black Monday I (9 March 2020)|Share prices fall sharply]] around the world, in response to [[2020 Russia\u2013Saudi Arabia oil price war|a new oil price war]] and the [[Socio-economic impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|impact of COVID-19]]. The DJIA plunges more than 2,000 points, the largest fall in its history up to that point.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-51796806|title=Black Monday: Shares face biggest fall since financial crisis|website=BBC News|language=en|date=March 9, 2020|access-date=March 9, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309034201/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-51796806|archive-date=March 9, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Oil prices]] also plunge by as much as 30 percent in early trading, the biggest fall since [[1990 oil price shock|1991]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Oil prices plunge as much as 30% after OPEC deal failure sparks price war |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/03/08/oil-plummets-30percent-as-opec-deal-failure-sparks-price-war-fears.html |accessdate=March 9, 2020 |agency=CNBC |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309000012/https://www.cnbc.com/2020/03/08/oil-plummets-30percent-as-opec-deal-failure-sparks-price-war-fears.html |archive-date=March 9, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* [[March 11]]\n** 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic: The [[World Health Organization]] declares the COVID-19 outbreak a [[pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-51839944|title=Coronavirus confirmed as pandemic by World Health Organization|website=BBC News|language=en|date=March 11, 2020|access-date=March 11, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311174102/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-51839944|archive-date=March 11, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n** [[Elizabeth II]] becomes the [[list of longest-reigning monarchs|longest-reigning monarch]] in the Americas, surpassing [[K\u02bcinich Janaab\u02bc Pakal|Pacal the Great]], who held that record for 68 years, from 615 to 683.{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n* [[March 12]] \u2013 [[2020 stock market crash#Black Thursday (12 March 2020)|Global stock markets crash]] due to continued concerns over COVID-19 and the U.S. [[Travel restrictions related to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic#Europe 2|travel ban]] on the [[Schengen Area]]. The Dow Jones Industrial Average goes into free fall, closing at over &minus;2,300 points, the worst losses for the index since [[Black Monday (1987)|1987]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Wearden (earlier)|first=Graeme|url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/live/2020/mar/12/stock-markets-tumble-trump-europe-travel-ban-ecb-christine-lagarde-business-live|title=Wall Street and FTSE 100 plunge on worst day since 1987 \u2013 as it happened|date=March 12, 2020|work=The Guardian|access-date=March 13, 2020|last2=Jolly (now)|first2=Jasper|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312093531/https://www.theguardian.com/business/live/2020/mar/12/stock-markets-tumble-trump-europe-travel-ban-ecb-christine-lagarde-business-live|archive-date=March 12, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[March 13]] \u2013 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic: The [[government of Nepal]] announces that [[Mount Everest]] will be closed to climbers and the public for the rest of the season due to concerns from the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic in Asia|COVID-19 pandemic in Asia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/mount-everest-coronavirus-closed-scli-intl/index.html|title=Mount Everest closed over coronavirus fears|publisher=[[CNN]]|date=March 13, 2020|access-date=March 20, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313194603/https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/mount-everest-coronavirus-closed-scli-intl/index.html|archive-date=March 13, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[March 14]] \u2013 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic: [[Spain]] goes into [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Spain|lockdown]] after COVID-19 cases in the country surge.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/coronavirus-spain-nationwide-lockdown/2020/03/14/3bec8690-6619-11ea-8a8e-5c5336b32760_story.html|title=Spain goes on nationwide lockdown as coronavirus cases surge|date=March 14, 2020|work=The Washington Post|access-date=March 14, 2020|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314203920/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/coronavirus-spain-nationwide-lockdown/2020/03/14/3bec8690-6619-11ea-8a8e-5c5336b32760_story.html|archive-date=March 14, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[March 15]] \u2013 Argentine president [[Alberto Fern\u00e1ndez]] declares preventive [[quarantine]] to gradual [[lockdown]] of the country being the first country aside from Spain and Italy to lockdown the country and the first one after few cases and no deaths were confirmed.\n* [[March 16]] \u2013 The DJIA [[2020 stock market crash#Black Monday II (16 March 2020)|falls by 2,997.10]], the single [[List of largest daily changes in the Dow Jones Industrial Average|largest point drop in history]] and the second largest percentage drop ever at 12.93 percent, an even greater crash than [[Wall Street Crash of 1929|Black Monday (1929)]]. This follows the U.S. [[Federal Reserve]] announcing that it will cut its target interest rate to 0\u20130.25 percent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/pressreleases/monetary20200315a.htm|title=Federal Reserve issues FOMC statement|website=Federal Reserve|date=March 15, 2020|access-date=March 17, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317021707/https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/pressreleases/monetary20200315a.htm|archive-date=March 17, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[March 17]]\n** 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic: The [[Government of the Islamic Republic of Iran|Iranian government]] warns that \"millions\" of its citizens may die from [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Iran|COVID-19]] as 988 people have thus far died in the country. 90 percent of the 18,000 COVID-19 cases in the [[Middle East]] have thus far occurred in Iran.<ref>{{cite web|website=AP|title=Iran warns virus could kill 'millions' in Islamic Republic|author1=NASSER KARIMI|author2=JON GAMBRELL|date=March 17, 2020|url=https://apnews.com/6e92d93551ee6c6ae51d0acaaad9eb32|access-date=March 17, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318132446/https://apnews.com/6e92d93551ee6c6ae51d0acaaad9eb32|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n** 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic: European leaders close the [[European Union|EU]]'s external and Schengen borders for at least 30 days in an effort to curb the COVID-19 pandemic.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/coronavirus/linksdossier/coronavirus-whats-happening-in-europe/|title=Coronavirus: What's happening in Europe|website=Euractiv|date=March 17, 2020|access-date=March 18, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318011326/https://www.euractiv.com/section/coronavirus/linksdossier/coronavirus-whats-happening-in-europe/|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n** 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic: [[UEFA]] postpones the [[Euro 2020]] [[association football]] tournament until summer 2021.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/19692/11958779/euro-2020-postponed-until-summer-of-2021-following-coronavirus-pandemic|title=Euro 2020 postponed until summer 2021; domestic leagues, UEFA competitions to be completed by June 30|publisher=[[Sky Sports]]|date=March 17, 2020|accessdate=March 26, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321001622/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/19692/11958779/euro-2020-postponed-until-summer-of-2021-following-coronavirus-pandemic|archive-date=March 21, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The next day, the [[European Broadcasting Union]] announces that the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2020]] will be cancelled due to COVID-19 in [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|Europe]], the first cancellation in the 64-year history of the contest.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://eurovision.tv/official-ebu-statement-and-faq-eurovision-song-contest-2020-cancellation|title=Eurovision 2020 cancellation for the first time in history of the contest.|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318142008/https://eurovision.tv/official-ebu-statement-and-faq-eurovision-song-contest-2020-cancellation|archive-date=March 18, 2020|access-date=}}</ref>\n* [[March 20]] \u2013 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic: The worldwide death toll from COVID-19 surpasses 10,000 as the total number of cases reaches a quarter of a million.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/live/world-51969508|title=Global coronavirus deaths pass 10,000|website=BBC News|date=March 20, 2020|access-date=March 20, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320044353/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/live/world-51969508|archive-date=March 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[March 23]] \u2013 Ten nations had joined the SOLIDARITY trial, a group sponsored by the [[World Health Organization]] to find a cure against COVID-19. Four European countries ([[Switzerland]], [[France]], [[Norway]] and [[Spain]]), two American countries ([[Argentina]] and [[Canada]]), three Asian countries ([[Iran]], [[Thailand]], [[Bahrain]]) and [[South Africa]] are leading efforts to finding a cure.\n* [[March 24]]\n** 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic: [[India]] goes into [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in India|lockdown]] for 21 days to contain COVID-19. The total number of people in the world facing some form of movement restriction now exceeds 2.6 billion, a third of the global population.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.yahoo.com/britain-lockdown-warns-pandemic-accelerating-051357601.html|work=Yahoo! News|title=A third of the world under vi