57.html |date=March 5, 2020 }} {{in lang|ru}}</ref>\n* [[March 6]]\n** [[Henri Richard]], Canadian [[Hockey Hall of Fame|Hall of Fame]] ice hockey player (b. [[1936]])<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.sportsnet.ca/hockey/nhl/canadiens-legend-henri-richard-passes-away-age-84/ |title=Canadiens legend Henri Richard passes away at age 84 |access-date=March 7, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306220137/https://www.sportsnet.ca/hockey/nhl/canadiens-legend-henri-richard-passes-away-age-84/ |archive-date=March 6, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n** [[McCoy Tyner]], American jazz pianist (b. [[1938]])<ref name=\"nytdeath\">{{cite news|last=Ratliff|first=Ben|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/06/arts/mccoy-tyner-dead.html|title=McCoy Tyner, Jazz Piano Powerhouse, Is Dead at 81|date=March 6, 2020|work=The New York Times|access-date=March 6, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[March 8]] \u2013 [[Max von Sydow]], Swedish-French actor (b. [[1929]])<ref>[https://www.aftonbladet.se/nojesbladet/a/jdAKPn/max-von-sydow-ar-dod/ Max von Sydow \u00e4r d\u00f6d] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309130247/https://www.aftonbladet.se/nojesbladet/a/jdAKPn/max-von-sydow-ar-dod |date=March 9, 2020 }} {{in lang|sv}}</ref>\n* [[March 9]] \u2013 [[Richard K. Guy]], British mathematician (b. [[1916]])<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://aperiodical.com/2020/03/richard-k-guy-1916-2020/ |title=Richard K. Guy (1916\u20132020) |access-date=March 10, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311000547/https://aperiodical.com/2020/03/richard-k-guy-1916-2020/ |archive-date=March 11, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* [[March 11]]\n** [[Charles Wuorinen]], American composer (b. [[1938]]) <ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/13/arts/music/charles-wuorinen-dead.html/ |title=Charles Wuorinen, Uncompromising Modernist Composer, Dies at 81 |access-date=March 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318031259/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/13/arts/music/charles-wuor