ossbow, a machete and Molotov cocktails, started firing in a classroom. The combination of machete attacks and crossbow arrows resulted in the death of one teacher and injury of four students. The boy apparently had a list with the names of 24 people he wanted to kill. This was the first ever attack in a school by perpetrated by a student in Spain's history. The attack came to an end after the student had a breakdown when his PE teacher managed to talk to him. The student then proceeded to sit down in a classroom until the police arrived. Under Spanish law, the boy is exempt from legal responsibility because he was under 14 years old at the time. He is now in a psychiatric clinic in his locality.\n|-\n|{{Dts|April 22, 2015}}\n| [[Desert Hot Springs, California]], United States\n| Suspect, 12\n|\n| 1 injured\n| A 13-year-old student was stabbed by a 12-year-old classmate at Painted Hills Middle School. The suspect was arrested. The victim received non-life threatening injuries.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.desertsun.com/story/news/crime_courts/2015/04/23/student-stabs-classmate-at-painted-hills-middle-school/26270911/|title=Police: Boy, 12, stabs Painted Hills Middle School classmate|website=desertsun.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|April 27, 2015}}\n| [[Lacey, Washington]], United States\n| Suspect, 16\n|\n| No injuries\n| In the [[North Thurston High School Shooting]], a student at [[North Thurston High School]] walked into the commons area and fired two shots into the ceiling from a .357 magnum pistol. Brady Olson, a teacher at the school, was able to tackle the student before they could turn the gun on other students. No one was injured or killed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.komonews.com/news/local/Gunman-at-North-Thurston-High-School-apprehended-by-staff-301426921.html|title=Gunman tackled by teacher after firing shots at N. Thurston H.S.|publisher=KOMO News|date=April 27, 2015|accessdate=April 27, 2015}}</ref><ref name=TribuneGun>{{cite news|title=Washington teacher who stopped shooter's first thought: Get the gun away|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/nationworld/chi-washington-school-shooting-teacher-20150428-story.html|accessdate=4 June 2015|agency=Tribune wire reports; AP|newspaper=[[Chicago Tribune]]|date=28 April 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|May 3, 2015}}\n|[[Midrand]], South Africa\n| \n| 1 dead\n| \n|A student was stabbed to death with scissors at Tsosoloso Ya Afrika secondary school.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.enca.com/south-africa/pupil-stabbed-death-school-0|title=Midrand schoolboys' fight ends tragically with scissors stabbing|website=www.enca.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|May 12, 2015}}\n| [[Jacksonville, Florida]], United States\n| Edgar Robles, 16\n|\n| 2 injured\n| Robles shot 15-year-olds Ayana Sherman and Shakayla Singleton while both were riding on a packed school bus. Before the shooting, Robles and two friends made threats towards the victims to fight them as part of revenge plot for a previous argument they had with them.<ref name=\"Action News JAX\">{{cite web|url=http://www.actionnewsjax.com/news/news/local/search-continues-16-year-old-suspect-school-bus-sh/nmHdP/|title=Search continues for 16-year-old suspect in school bus shooting|publisher=Action News JAX|date=May 15, 2015|accessdate=May 18, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|May 18, 2015}}\n| [[Shellbrook, Saskatchewan]], Canada \n| Michael Rudolph, 19\n|\n| 1 injured\n| A 17-year-old female student was stabbed and seriously injured at W.P. Sandin Public School. 19-year-old Michael Rudolph was arrested and charged with assault.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/saskatchewan/man-19-charged-in-alleged-shellbrook-school-stabbing-1.3078975|title=Man, 19, charged in alleged Shellbrook school stabbing|website=cbc.ca}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|May 29, 2015}}\n| [[Ennerdale, South Africa]]\n| Three suspects\n| 1 dead\n|\n| A 21-year-old man trespassing on school grounds was stabbed to death by three high school pupils.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.enca.com/south-africa/ennerdale-pupils-arrested-after-fatal-stabbing|title=Ennerdale pupils arrested after fatal stabbing|website=www.enca.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|June 1, 2015}}\n| [[Upper Marlboro, Maryland]], United States\n| Unnamed suspect, 14\n| \n| 1 injured\n| A 16-year-old was seriously injured after being stabbed during a fight at [[Frederick Douglass High School (Prince George's County, Maryland)|Frederick Douglass High School]]. A 14-year-old was arrested.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wjla.com/news/crime/2-students-injured-in-stabbing-at-frederick-douglass-high-in-md--114442|title=Student seriously injured in stabbing at Frederick Douglass High School in Maryland|first=Brad Bell, John Gonzalez, ABC 7|last=News|website=wjla.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|June 2, 2015}}\n| [[Winnipeg, Manitoba]], Canada \n| Unnamed suspect, 17\n| 1 dead\n| \n| A 17-year-old Brett Bourne was stabbed to death in front of [[Kelvin High School]], during a fight. Another 17-year-old was charged with second-degree murder.<ref>[http://www.winnipegsun.com/2015/08/13/kelvin-schoolyard-scuffle-turned-deadly-court-hears Kelvin schoolyard scuffle turned deadly, court hears 9], ''[[Winnipeg Sun]]'', August 13, 2015.</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|June 11, 2015}}\n| [[Bradford]], United Kingdom\n| Student, 14\n|\n| 1 injured\n| A 14-year-old boy was charged with attempted murder after a teacher was stabbed in the stomach in a classroom full of pupils.\nBradford crown court heard that the attack was premeditated and partially racially motivated. Uzomah is black and the boy, who is of Pakistani origin, regularly referred to him \"by the epithet beginning with the letter N\"\n<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2015/jun/12/bradford-school-stabbing-boy-charged-attempted-murder-teacher|title=Bradford school stabbing: boy charged with attempted murder of teacher |publisher=[[The Guardian]]|website=theguardian.com |date=12 June 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|August 25, 2015}}\n| [[Philippi, West Virginia]], Unite