5|title=Page Not Found|website=whec.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| May 11, 2009\n| [[Sankt Augustin]],<br>[[North Rhine-Westphalia]],<br>Germany\n| Tanja Otto, 16\n|\n| 1 injured\n| A 16-year-old student, Tanja Otto, entered the Albert Einstein [[Gymnasium (school)|gymnasium]] (high school), in [[Sankt Augustin]], Germany, carrying knives, [[incendiary bombs|incendiary explosives]], [[gunpowder]], a [[flamethrower]], and an [[air gun|air-powered pistol]]. Otto attempted to [[arson|torch]] the school but was confronted by another student in the girls' restroom, who Otto then slashed in the hand. The victim's thumb was severed and she was treated a local hospital.<ref name=\"skynews511\">{{cite news|title=Teen Girl Hunted After German School Stabbing|date=2009-05-11|url =http://news.sky.com/skynews/Home/World-News/Germany-School-Knife-Attacker-On-The-Loose-At-Least-One-Girl-Injured/Article/200905215279355?lpos=World_News_Top_Stories_Header_1&lid=ARTICLE_15279355_Germany%3A_School_Knife_Attacker_On_The_Loose%2C_At_Least_One_Girl_Injured|work=[[Sky News]]|accessdate = 2009-05-11}}</ref><ref name=\"thelocal511\">{{cite news|title=Teen girl who stabbed student planned arson|date=2009-05-11|url =http://www.thelocal.de/national/20090511-19203.html|work=[[The Local]]|accessdate = 2009-05-11}}</ref><ref name=\"canwest511\">{{cite news|title=German girl tries to set school on fire|date=2009-05-11|url=http://www.canada.com/news/German+girl+tries+school+fire/1584824/story.html|work=[[Canwest News Service|Canwest News]]|accessdate=2009-05-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090725082323/http://www.canada.com/news/German+girl+tries+school+fire/1584824/story.html|archive-date=2009-07-25|url-status=dead}}</ref> Otto subsequently fled the school, and was apprehended several hours later by police.<ref name=\"thelocal512\">{{cite news|title=Homemade bomb found in teen school attacker's room|date=2009-05-12|url =http://www.thelocal.de/national/20090512-19217.html|work=[[The Local]]|accessd