{"title_page": "Maya Yoshida", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2012}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Maya Yoshida\n| fullname       = Maya Yoshida<ref>{{cite web|title=Premier League Clubs submit Squad Lists |url=http://www.premierleague.com/content/dam/premierleague/site-content/News/publications/squad-lists/Premier-League-squad-lists-September-2014.pdf |publisher=Premier League |accessdate=2 January 2015 |date=3 September 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141022192726/http://www.premierleague.com/content/dam/premierleague/site-content/News/publications/squad-lists/Premier-League-squad-lists-September-2014.pdf |archivedate=22 October 2014 }}</ref>\n| image          = Maya Yoshida.jpg\n| caption        = Yoshida lining up for [[Japan national football team|Japan]] at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1988|8|24|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Nagasaki]], Japan\n| height         = 1.89 m<ref>{{cite web|title=Maya Yoshida|url=https://www.fifa.com/confederationscup/players/player=271253/index.html|work=fifa.com|publisher=[[FIFA]]|accessdate=15 January 2014}}</ref>\n| currentclub    = [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]]<br>(On loan from [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]])\n| clubnumber     = 34\n| position       = [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|Centre back]]\n| youthyears1    = 2001\u20132006\n| youthclubs1    = [[Nagoya Grampus]]\n| years1         = 2007\u20132010 | clubs1 = [[Nagoya Grampus]]               | caps1 = 71 | goals1 = 5\n| years2         = 2010\u20132012 | clubs2 = [[VVV-Venlo]]                    | caps2 = 54 | goals2 = 5\n| years3         = 2012\u2013     | clubs3 = [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] | caps3 = 154| goals3 = 6\n| years4         = 2020\u2013     | clubs4 = \u2192 [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]] (loan)   | caps4 =  0 | goals4 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2008\u20132012 | nationalteam1  = [[Japan national under-23 football team|Japan U23]] | nationalcaps1 = 12 | nationalgoals1 = 1\n| nationalyears2 = 2010\u2013     | nationalteam2  = [[Japan national football team|Japan]]              | nationalcaps2 = 100 | nationalgoals2 = 11\n|medaltemplates=\n{{MedalCountry|{{fb|JPN}}}}\n{{Medal|Competition|[[AFC Asian Cup]]}}\n{{Medal|W|[[2011 AFC Asian Cup|2011 Qatar]]|}}\n{{Medal|RU|[[2019 AFC Asian Cup|2019 United Arab Emirates]]|}}\n| club-update    = 04:19, 1 February 2020 (UTC)\n| ntupdate       = 13:35, 14 November 2019 (UTC)\n}}\n{{nihongo|'''Maya Yoshida'''|\u5409\u7530 \u9ebb\u4e5f|Yoshida Maya|born 24 August 1988}} is a Japanese [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre back]] for Serie A side [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]], on loan from {{English football updater|Southamp}} club [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]], and captains the [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]].\n\n==Club career==\n===Nagoya Grampus===\nBorn in [[Nagasaki]], Japan, Yoshida began playing football at Nanling FC in his second year at elementary school.<ref name=\"Yoshida Brother\"/><ref name=\"Yoshida Brother2\"/> His older brother, Honami, played an important role to his football career when he searched on the internet for [[Nagoya Grampus]]\u2019s U-15 and this led Yoshida to join the U-15 side.<ref name=\"Yoshida Brother\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nagasaki-np.co.jp/sports/2008/gorin/kikaku1/05.html|title=\u30b5\u30c3\u30ab\u30fc\u7537\u5b50 \u5409\u7530\u9ebb\u4e5f\uff08\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u30b0\u30e9\u30f3\u30d1\u30b9\uff09|publisher=Nagasaki|language=Japanese|date=22 July 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080801190827/https://www.nagasaki-np.co.jp/sports/2008/gorin/kikaku1/05.html|archivedate=5 April 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> Once Yoshida has joined, Yoshida relocated to Nagoya to be close at Nagoya Grampus and attended Toyota High School.<ref name=\"Yoshida Brother\"/><ref name=\"Yoshida Brother2\"/><ref>{{cite news|title=\u30b5\u30c3\u30ab\u30fc\u5409\u7530\u9ebb\u4e5f\u9078\u624b\u3001\u9ad8\u6821\u6642\u4ee3\u304b\u3089\u4e00\u76ee\u7f6e\u304b\u308c\u308b\u5b58\u5728|url=https://www.nikkei.com/article/DGXNASFD04009_U2A800C1CN8000/|publisher=Nikkei|language=Japanese|date=5 August 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nAfter spending five years at Nagoya Grampus Youth Academy, he was promoted to the first team in the 2007 season, having signed his first professional contract.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u306b4\u9078\u624b\u52a0\u5165\u5185\u5b9a|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?21441-2335-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=2 November 2006|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9ebb\u4e5f\u3001\u4f1a\u898b\u3067\u306e\u6e3e\u8eab\u30ae\u30e3\u30b0\u3092\u5f01\u89e3\u300c\u4eca\u56de\u306f\u305f\u307e\u305f\u307e\u30b9\u30d9\u3063\u305f\u3060\u3051\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?115665-119882-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=13 June 2013|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Yoshida joined the club\u2019s first team training soon after and started out in a defensive midfielder when playing for Grampus's youth team, but was converted to a centre back.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chunichi.co.jp/chuspo/hold/grampus/news/2007/200702/CK2007032202103071.html|title=\u30b0\u30e9\u65b0\u4eba\u7d39\u4ecb\u3000\u4e03\u4eba\u306e\u4f8d\u304c\u6b74\u53f2\u3092\u4f5c\u308b|publisher=Chunichi|language=Japanese|date=9 February  2007|accessdate=5 April 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101005064650/https://www.chunichi.co.jp/chuspo/hold/grampus/news/2007/200702/CK2007032202103071.html|archivedate=5 April 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> After spending months on the substitute bench, Yoshida finally made his debut for the club, coming on as a second half substitute, in a 2\u20131 loss against [[Oita Trinita]] on 3 May 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nagoya-grampus.jp/backnumber/result/2007/0503/result.html|title=2007 J\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\u30ef\u30f3\uff1a\u30bb\u30af\u30b7\u30e7\u30f39|publisher=Nagoya Grampus|language=Japanese|date=3 May 2007|accessdate=5 April 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200331210504/https://nagoya-grampus.jp/backnumber/result/2007/0503/result.html|archivedate=5 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Since then, he became a first team regular for the side, playing in the centre\u2013back position.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nagoya-grampus.jp/backnumber/result/2007/0526/nagare.html|title=2007 J\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f31\uff1a\u30e9\u30a6\u30f3\u30c913|publisher=Nagoya Grampus|language=Japanese|date=26 May 2007|accessdate=5 April 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200401180940/https://nagoya-grampus.jp/backnumber/result/2007/0526/nagare.html|archivedate=5 April 2020|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://nagoya-grampus.jp/backnumber/result/2007/0825/result.html|title=2007 J\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f31\uff1a22\u30e9\u30a6\u30f3\u30c9|publisher=Nagoya Grampus|language=Japanese|date=25 August 2007|accessdate=5 April 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200401183824/https://nagoya-grampus.jp/backnumber/result/2007/0825/result.html|archivedate=5 April 2020|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://nagoya-grampus.jp/backnumber/result/2007/1118/result.html|title=2007 J\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f31\uff1a32\u30e9\u30a6\u30f3\u30c9|publisher=Nagoya Grampus|language=Japanese|date=18 November 2007|accessdate=5 April 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200401184100/https://nagoya-grampus.jp/backnumber/result/2007/1118/result.html|archivedate=5 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 5 November 2007 when Yoshida scored his first Nagoya Grampus goal, in a 3\u20131 win against [[Thespakusatsu Gunma|Thespa Kusatsu]] in the fourth round of the Emperor\u2019s Cup.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nagoya-grampus.jp/backnumber/result/2007/1104/result.html|title=\u30c6\u30b9\u30d1\u8349\u6d251-3\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u30b0\u30e9\u30f3\u30d1\u30b9|publisher=Nagoya Grampus|language=Japanese|date=4 November 2007|accessdate=5 April 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200401182008/https://nagoya-grampus.jp/backnumber/result/2007/1104/result.html|archivedate=5 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> At the end of the 2007 season, he went on to make twenty\u2013four appearances and scoring once in all competitions.\n\nIn the 2008 season, Yoshida began to feature in the starting line-up for most of the league matches with his Serbian teammate [[Milo\u0161 Bajalica]].<ref>{{cite news|title=J1\u7b2c1\u7bc0(3\u67088\u65e5)\u540d\u53e4\u5c4bvs\u4eac\u90fd \u8a66\u5408\u7d50\u679c|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?34265-14917-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=6 March 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u306e19\u6b73DF\u5409\u7530\u300c\u9ad8\u539f\u3055\u3093\u6291\u3048\u308c\u3070\u81ea\u4fe1\u304c\u3064\u304f\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?34601-15288-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=14 March 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=10\u4eba\u306e\u9593\u306b\u5931\u70b9\u3001PK\u5931\u6557\u3068F\u6771\u4eac\u306f\u4e0d\u904b\u306a\u6557\u6226\u3001\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u306f4\u6226\u3076\u308a\u52dd\u5229(F\u6771\u4eacvs\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b)|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?36976-17666-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=6 May 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=[\u5317\u4eac\u3078\u306e\u9053(1)]DF\u5409\u7530\u9ebb\u4e5f(\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b)|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?39247-20075-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=2 July 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> He started the season well when he helped the side go on an unbeaten with seven matches in all competitions. <ref>{{cite news|title=\u30e8\u30f3\u30bb\u30f3\u3001\u5c0f\u5ddd\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u3067\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u4eca\u5b63\u521d\u52dd\u5229!\u6d66\u548cvs\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u8a66\u5408\u7d50\u679c|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?34659-15338-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=15 March 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=2\u4f4d\u30fb3\u4f4d\u5bfe\u6c7a\u5236\u3057\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u304c4\u9023\u52dd!(\u540d\u53e4\u5c4bvs\u6a2a\u6d5cFM\u8a66\u5408\u8a18\u9332\u30fb\u30b3\u30e1\u30f3\u30c8)|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?35611-16267-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=5 April 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u6749\u672c\u306e\u516c\u5f0f\u62264\u6226\u9023\u7d9a\u5f3e\u3067\u9006\u8ee2!\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u304c\u516c\u5f0f\u62267\u9023\u52dd(\u540d\u53e4\u5c4bvs\u5343\u8449 \u8a66\u5408\u8a18\u9332&\u30b3\u30e1\u30f3\u30c8)|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?36177-16858-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=19 April 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Yoshida continued to feature in the first team until he was called up to the Japan U23 squad in July.<ref>{{cite news|title=2\u4f4d\u30fb\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u52dd\u3061\u70b93\u7372\u5f97\u306a\u3089\u305a(\u540d\u53e4\u5c4bvs\u795e\u6238 \u8a66\u5408\u8a18\u9332&\u30b3\u30e1\u30f3\u30c8)|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?37163-17867-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=10 May 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u2605\u300c\u3042\u306a\u305f\u306e\u9078\u3076J1\u524d\u534a\u6226\u30d9\u30b9\u30c8\u30a4\u30ec\u30d6\u30f3\u300d\u7d50\u679c\u767a\u8868|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?38631-19462-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=16 June 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u304c\u30e8\u30f3\u30bb\u30f3\u306e\u6c7a\u52dd\u70b9\u3067\u9023\u6557\u30b9\u30c8\u30c3\u30d7\u3001\u67cf\u306f\u516c\u5f0f\u622610\u8a66\u5408\u3076\u308a\u9ed2\u661f(\u540d\u53e4\u5c4bvs\u67cf \u8a66\u5408\u8a18\u9332&\u30b3\u30e1\u30f3\u30c8)|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?39625-20457-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=12 July 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> After Japan U23\u2019s elimination in the Summer Olympics, it wasn\u2019t until on 23 August 2008 when Yoshida returned to the starting line-up against [[Kashima Antlers]] and scored his first goal of the season, in a 2\u20131 win.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u304c\u30ab\u30b7\u30de\u3067\u5ff5\u9858\u306e\u521d\u52dd\u5229!\u9e7f\u5cf6\u306f\u9996\u4f4d\u9665\u843d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?41457-22358-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=23 August 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Following this, he lost his first team place and was placed on the substitute bench for the next five matches, leading his playing time to be reduced.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u30fb\u5409\u7530\u304c\u30ca\u30d3\u30b9\u30b3\u676fV\u5ba3\u8a00|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?41852-22767-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=1 September 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u5927\u5206vs.\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b \u8a66\u5408\u8a18\u9332|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?42103-23016-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=7 September 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u540d\u53e4\u5c4bvs\u6771\u4eacV \u8a66\u5408\u8a18\u9332|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?43438-24314-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=5 October 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Yoshida\u2019s second goal then came on 2 November 2008 against [[FC Gifu]] in the fourth round of the Emperor\u2019s Cup and helped them win 1\u20130.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u304c\u683c\u4e0b\u306b\u5927\u82e6\u6226\uff0f\u5929\u7687\u676f|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/f-sc-tp0-20081102-425532.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=2 November 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> By mid\u2013October, he regained his first team place for the remaining matches of the season and helped the side finished third place in the league.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u6a2a\u6d5cFMvs\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u306f\u6c7a\u3081\u624b\u306a\u304f\u30b9\u30b3\u30a2\u30ec\u30b9\u30c9\u30ed\u30fc|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?44066-24978-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=19 October 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u30d4\u30af\u30b7\u30fc\u76e3\u7763\u304c\u5c45\u6b8b\u308a\u30b7\u30e5\u30fc\u30c8\u7df4\u7fd2|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/f-sc-tp0-20081204-436724.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=4 December 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u5927\u5206vs.\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b \u8a66\u5408\u8a18\u9332|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?46563-27525-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=6 December 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> For his performance, Yoshida was award Rookie of the Year at the 14th Aichi Toyota \"Grand Pass Rankle Award\".<ref>{{cite news|title=\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u30fb\u5c0f\u5ddd\u4f73\u7d14\u304c\u30b0\u30e9\u30f3\u30d1\u30b9\u30e9\u30f3\u30af\u30eb\u8cde\u3067\u6700\u512a\u79c0\u9078\u624b\u306b|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?45933-26903-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=25 November 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> At the end of the 2008 season, he went on to make twenty\u2013nine appearances and scoring two times in all competitions.\n\nAt the start of the 2009 season, Yoshida switched number shirt to four.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\uff24\uff26\u5409\u7530\u3001\u677e\u5742\u306e\u6559\u3048\u3067\u5168\u6226\u51fa\u5834\u3060|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/p-sc-tp0-20090202-456503.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=2 February 2009|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> He scored [[Nagoya Grampus]]'s historical first goal in the [[AFC Champions League]] in the game against [[Ulsan Hyundai FC|Ulsan Hyundai Horang-i]] on 10 March 2009.<ref>{{cite news|title=[ACL]\u521d\u53c2\u6226\u306e\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u306f3\u767a\u9006\u8ee2\u3067\u521d\u9663\u98fe\u308b|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?50807-32006-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=10 March 2009|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Yoshida continued to regain his first team place for the side, playing in the centre\u2013back position.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u7b2c2\u7bc0(3\u670814\u65e5)\u5c71\u5f62vs\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u30d7\u30ec\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc&\u4e88\u60f3\u5148\u767a|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?50912-32105-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=12 March 2009|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u7121\u6557\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u306b\u571f\u3001\u5ddd\u5d0eF\u304c\u4eca\u5b63\u521d\u52dd\u5229|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?51850-33120-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=4 April 2009|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=[ACL]20\u6b73\u306e\u65b0\u5ddd\u304c\u30d7\u30ed\u521d\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u3001\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u306f\u7121\u6557\u3067\u6c7a\u52ddT\u3078|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?54086-35449-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=20 May 2009|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> A month later on 26 April 2009, he scored his second goal of the season, in a 2\u20131 win against [[Yokohama F. Marinos]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5c0f\u5ddd\u306eFK\u5f3e\u3067\u9006\u8ee2\u3001\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u304c4\u4f4d\u6d6e\u4e0a|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?52831-34165-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=26 April 2009|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> However, Yoshida suffered a calf injury that saw him sidelined for two weeks.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5409\u7530\u304c\u8089\u96e2\u308c\u3001\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u306f\u4e21CB\u304c\u6b20\u5834\u3078|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?56213-38354-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=5 July 2009|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Yoshida made his first team return on 18 July 2009 and started the whole game, in a 1\u20131 draw against [[Kyoto Sanga FC|Kyoto Sanga]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nagoya-grampus.jp/game/result/2009/07182009j118vsfc/|title=2009J1\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u7b2c18\u7bc0\uff1a\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u30b0\u30e9\u30f3\u30d1\u30b9vs\u4eac\u90fd\u30b5\u30f3\u30acF.C.|publisher=Nagoya Grampus|language=Japanese|date=18 July 2009|accessdate=5 April 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200402193434/https://nagoya-grampus.jp/game/result/2009/07182009j118vsfc/|archivedate=5 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>  He scored his third goal of the season, in a 2\u20131 win against [[FC Tokyo]] eleven days later on 29 July 2009, but the club was eliminated in the J.League Cup following a 6\u20133 on aggregate.<ref>{{cite news|title=F\u6771\u4eac\u300111\u6226\u3076\u308a\u6557\u6226\u30825\u5e74\u3076\u308a\u306e4\u5f37|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?57357-39898-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=29 July 2009|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Yoshida later added two more goals throughout September, scoring against [[Kashiwa Reysol]] and [[Kawasaki Frontale]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u67cf\u30a2\u30a6\u30a7\u30fc\u30673\u767a\u52dd\u5229\u300115\u4f4d\u3068\u306e\u66ab\u5b9a\u52dd\u3061\u70b9\u5dee\u306f2\u306b|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?59236-42480-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=12 September 2009|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=[ACL]\u30b1\u30cd\u30c7\u30a3\u304c\u6b7b\u95d8\u306b\"\u8e74\u308a\"\u3001\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u304cJ\u5bfe\u6c7a\u5236\u3057\u6e96\u6c7a\u52dd\u3078|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?59905-43422-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=30 September 2009|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Since returning to the first team, Yoshida regained his first team place for the remaining matches of the season.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6vs\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b \u8a66\u5408\u5f8c\u306e\u9078\u624b\u30b3\u30e1\u30f3\u30c8|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?59758-43220-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=27 September 2009|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=[\u6226\u8a55]\u540d\u53e4\u5c4bDF\u306e\u201c\u8db3\u4e0b\u201d\u304c\u4e0d\u5b89\u3002ACL\u306e\u8ab2\u984c\u3060|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?60662-44436-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=18 October 2009|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<vr>{{cite news|title=[ACL]\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u306f\u6e96\u6c7a\u52dd\u3067\u5922\u6563\u308b\u3001\u65e5\u672c\u52e23\u9023\u8987\u306a\u3089\u305a|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?61107-45038-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=28 October 2009|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> He later added two more goals throughout October.<ref>{{cite news|title=F\u6771\u4eac\u30fb\u77f3\u5ddd\u304c14\u5f97\u70b9\u76ee!\u9006\u8ee2\u52dd\u3061\u30677\u4f4d\u306b\u6d6e\u4e0a|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?60074-43635-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=4 October 2009|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u6a2a\u6d5cFM\u304c\u72e9\u91ce\u306e\u30ed\u30b9\u30bf\u30a4\u30e0\u5f3e\u3067\u9006\u8ee2\u52dd\u3061|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?60647-44420-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=17 October 2009|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Yoshida scored his eighth goal of the season, in a 3\u20131 win against [[J\u00fabilo Iwata]] in the fourth round of the Emperor\u2019s Cup.<ref>{{cite news|title=[\u5929\u7687\u676f]\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u304c3\u500d\u4ee5\u4e0a\u306e\u30b7\u30e5\u30fc\u30c8\u3092\u6d74\u3073\u305b\u3066\u78d0\u7530\u306b\u52dd\u5229|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?61830-46054-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=15 November 2009|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> He later helped the club to reach the Emperor\u2019s Cup final after beating [[Shimizu S-Pulse]] 5\u20134 on penalty shoot\u2013out following a 1\u20131 draw throughout 120 minutes.<ref>{{cite news|title=[\u5929\u7687\u676f]\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u304cPK\u6226\u306e\u6fc0\u95d8\u3092\u5236\u305710\u5e74\u3076\u308a\u6c7a\u52dd\u9032\u51fa|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?63629-48564-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=29 December 2009|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> However, he started in the [[2009_Emperor%27s_Cup#Final|Emperor\u2019s Cup Final]] against [[Gamba Osaka]], as Nagoya Grampus lost 4\u20131 in what turns out to be his last appearance for the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nagoya-grampus.jp/game/result/2010/010189vs-1/index.html|title=\u7b2c89\u56de\u5929\u7687\u676f\u5168\u65e5\u672c\u30b5\u30c3\u30ab\u30fc\u9078\u624b\u6a29\u5927\u4f1a\u6c7a\u52dd\uff1a\u30ac\u30f3\u30d0\u5927\u962avs\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u30b0\u30e9\u30f3\u30d1\u30b9|publisher=Nagoya Grampus|language=Japanese|date=1 January 2010|accessdate=5 April 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200402202202/https://nagoya-grampus.jp/game/result/2010/010189vs-1/index.html|archivedate=5 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>At the end of the 2009 season, Yoshida went on to make forty\u2013eight appearances and scoring eight times in all competitions.\n\n===VVV-Venlo===\n[[File:Yoshida Maya blr.jpg|thumb|right|300px|Yoshida pictured during his time at [[VVV-Venlo]] at the fan gatherings.]]\n\nIn December 2009, it was announced that Yoshida had transferred to Dutch club [[VVV-Venlo]], signing a three\u2013year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ad.nl/ad/nl/1452/VVV-Venlo/article/detail/464932/2010/02/20/Yoshida-mag-voetballen-voor-VVV.dhtml|title=Yoshida mag voetballen voor VVV|publisher=Algemeen Dagblad|language=Japanese|date=20 February 2010|accessdate=5 April 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100225092547/http://www.ad.nl/ad/nl/1452/VVV-Venlo/article/detail/464932/2010/02/20/Yoshida-mag-voetballen-voor-VVV.dhtml|archivedate=5 April 2020|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite web|url=http://www.wsn.com/2009/12/28/football/news/asia/nagoyas-yoshida-to-join-venlo_26909/|title=Nagoya's Yoshida to join Venlo|publisher=WSN|date=2 January 2010|accessdate=28 December 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100102014453/http://www.wsn.com/2009/12/28/football/news/asia/nagoyas-yoshida-to-join-venlo_26909/|archivedate=5 April 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> He had desired to play for a club in Europe since he was young. [[Keisuke Honda]], who was his teammate at [[Nagoya Grampus]], introduced his agent, [[Tetsuro Kiyooka]] to support his future vision.<ref name=\"Yoshida V-Venlo\">{{cite news|title=Venlo chief eyes new Japanese talent|url=http://www.japantimes.co.jp/sports/2014/04/03/soccer/venlo-chief-eyes-new-japanese-talent/|publisher=The Japan Times|date=3 April 2014}}</ref> Indeed, Yoshida followed the footsteps of Keisuke Honda who also played for VVV-Venlo before he joined them.<ref name=\"Yoshida V-Venlo 2009\">{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/11/transfer-zone/2009/12/29/1714116/japan-defender-maya-yoshida-leaves-nagoya-grampus-for-vvv|title=Japan Defender Maya Yoshida Leaves Nagoya Grampus For VVV Venlo|publisher=Goal.com|date=29 December 2009|accessdate=15 July 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100204221825/http://www.goal.com/en/news/11/transfer-zone/2009/12/29/1714116/japan-defender-maya-yoshida-leaves-nagoya-grampus-for-vvv|archivedate=5 April 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> However, Yoshida\u2019s start to VVV-Venlo career suffered a setback when he fractured his foot and left him sidelined for the rest of the 2009\u201310 season.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u4e0d\u904b! VVV\u30fb\u5409\u7530\u304c\u521d\u5b9f\u6226\u3067\u9aa8\u6298|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?64170-49319-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=13 January 2010|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Yoshida hervat groepstraining bij VVV Venlo|url=https://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbalnieuws/140791/yoshida-hervat-groepstraining-bij-vvv-venlo/|publisher=FC Update|language=Dutch|date=10 March 2010|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nAt the start of the 2010\u201311 season, Yoshida continued to recover from his fractured foot.<ref>{{cite news|title=VVV Venlo heeft Japanner Yoshida bijna terug|url=https://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbalnieuws/157873/vvv-venlo-heeft-japanner-yoshida-bijna-terug/|publisher=FC Update|language=Dutch|date=30 September 2010|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Yoshida meldt zich eindelijk weer bij VVV Venlo|url=https://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbalnieuws/158815/yoshida-meldt-zich-eindelijk-weer-bij-vvv/|publisher=FC Update|language=Dutch|date=12 October 2010|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 30 October 2010 when he made his VVV-Venlo debut, coming on as a 75th minute substitute, and set up the club\u2019s third goal of the game, in a 5\u20133 loss against [[FC Groningen]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u524d\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u306e\u5409\u7530\u304c\u5f85\u671b\u306e\u30aa\u30e9\u30f3\u30c0\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc! \u30a2\u30b7\u30b9\u30c8\u3082\u8a18\u9332!!!|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?75725-66029-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=31 October 2010|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Since making his debut, Yoshida quickly became a first team regular for the side.<ref>{{cite news|title=Basisdebuut Yoshida, weinig zorgen Van Arum|url=https://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbalnieuws/161618/basisdebuut-yoshida-weinig-zorgen-van-arum/|publisher=FC Update|language=Dutch|date=12 November 2010|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=VVV\u5409\u7530\u304c\u53e4\u5de3\u30fb\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u512a\u52dd\u306b\u559c\u3073\u306e\u58f0|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?76946-67843-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=24 November 2010|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=VVV\u3001\u5409\u7530\u5148\u767a\u5f8c\u521d\u52dd\u3061\u70b9|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?77703-68900-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=11 December 2010|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> After spending January with Japan in the Asian Cup and winning the tournament, he made his first team return, starting the whole game, in a 3\u20130 win against [[NAC Breda]] on 5 February 2011.<ref>{{cite news|title=VVV geeft kampioen Yoshida warm onthaal|url=https://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbalnieuws/168373/vvv-geeft-kampioen-yoshida-warm-onthaal/|publisher=FC Update|language=Dutch|date=2 February 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Yoshida later regained his first team place for the remaining matches of the season, as VVV-Venlo qualified for the relegation play\u2013offs.<ref>{{cite news|title=[\u30aa\u30e9\u30f3\u30c0]VVV\u9023\u6557\u3001\u5409\u7530&\u30ab\u30ec\u30f3\u306f\u51fa\u5834|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?80792-73223-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=21 February 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=[\u30aa\u30e9\u30f3\u30c0]VVV\u306f\u964d\u683cPO\u570f\u5185\u78ba\u5b9a\u3001\u5409\u7530&\u30ab\u30ec\u30f3\u306f\u63c3\u3063\u3066\u5148\u767a|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?83125-76747-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=17 April 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u5bae\u5e02\u521d\u306e\u6b20\u5834\u3067\u65e5\u672c\u4eba\u5bfe\u6c7a\u306a\u3089\u305a\u3001VVV\u306f\u81ea\u52d5\u964d\u683c\u56de\u907f\u3001\u30d5\u30a7\u30a4\u30a8\u306fEL\u7d76\u671b\u7684|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?83806-77652-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=1 May 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> He started all the four matches in the relegation play\u2013offs and helped the club retain their Eredivisie league status.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u30ab\u30ec\u30f3\u5148\u5236\uff01\uff36\uff36\uff36\u304c\u5148\u52dd\uff0f\u30aa\u30e9\u30f3\u30c0|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/world/news/f-sc-tp3-20110520-778419.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=20 May 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\uff36\uff36\uff36\u30ab\u30ec\u30f3\u9023\u767a\uff01\uff13\u56de\u6226\u3078\uff0f\u30aa\u30e9\u30f3\u30c0|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/world/news/f-sc-tp3-20110522-779729.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=22 May 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u30ab\u30ec\u30f3\u597d\u6a5f\u3064\u304f\u308a\uff36\uff36\uff36\u5148\u52dd\uff0f\u30aa\u30e9\u30f3\u30c0|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/world/news/f-sc-tp3-20110527-781880.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=27 May 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u5409\u7530&\u30ab\u30ec\u30f3\u306eVVV\u30011\u90e8\u6b8b\u7559\u304c\u6c7a\u5b9a|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?85211-79506-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=30 May 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> At the end of the 2010\u201311 season, Yoshida went on to make twenty\u2013four appearances in all competitions.\n\nAt the start of the 2011\u201312 season, Yoshida continued to retain his first team place for the side, playing in the centre\u2013back position.<ref>{{cite news|title=VVVvs\u30e6\u30c8\u30ec\u30d2\u30c8 \u8a66\u5408\u5f8c\u306e\u5409\u7530\u30fb\u30ab\u30ec\u30f3\u306e\u4e00\u554f\u4e00\u7b54|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?88536-83812-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=7 August 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=VVV\u304c\u30c9\u30ed\u30fc\u3001\u5409\u7530&\u30ab\u30ec\u30f3\u306f\u30d5\u30eb\u51fa\u5834|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?89124-84658-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=22 August 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u5409\u7530\u304c\u958b\u5e55\u304b\u308918\u6226\u9023\u7d9a\u5148\u767a\u306eVVV\u306f\u9006\u8ee2\u52dd\u5229\u3001\u30ab\u30ec\u30f3\u306f\u4eca\u5b63\u521d\u306e\u6b20\u5834|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?95100-93509-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=23 January 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> He scored a bicycle kick goal for VVV-Venlo off a corner kick on 11 September 2011 against [[PSV Eindhoven]], as the match ended in a 3\u20133 draw.<ref>{{cite news|title=PSV blijft op 3-3 steken tegen VVV Venlo|url=https://psv.supporters.nl/nieuws/artikel/25880/PSV-blijft-op-3-3-steken-tegen-VVV|publisher=PSV Supporters News|language=Dutch|date=11 September 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> This goal was awarded as \"Goal of the Season 2011\u20132012\" of the [[Eredivisie]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Yoshida aiming for first Saints goal|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/10383308.yoshida-aiming-for-first-saints-goal/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=26 April 2013|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>The Yoshida scored his second goal of the season, in a 4\u20131 win against [[RKC Waalwijk]] on 22 October 2011.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5409\u7530\u304c\u5148\u5236\u30d8\u30c3\u30c9\u3067\u4eca\u5b632\u70b9\u76ee!!VVV\u306f\u958b\u5e5510\u6226\u76ee\u3067\u5f85\u671b\u306e\u521d\u52dd\u5229|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?91639-88259-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=22 October 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 18 February 2012 when he scored his third goal of the season, in a 4\u20131 win against [[De Graafschap]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5409\u7530\u304c12\u6226\u3076\u308a\u4eca\u5b633\u70b9\u76ee\u306e\u6c7a\u52dd\u30d8\u30c3\u30c9\u3001VVV\u304c\u30a2\u30a6\u30a7\u30fc\u521d\u52dd\u5229\u3067\u4eca\u5b63\u521d\u306e\u9023\u52dd|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?95866-94764-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=18 February 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Yoshida\u2019s fourth goal of the season came on 3 March 2012, in a 2\u20131 win against [[NAC Breda]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5f8c\u534a40\u5206\u306b\u30ab\u30ec\u30f3!42\u5206\u306b\u5409\u7530!\u521d\u306e\u30a2\u30d9\u30c3\u30af\u5f3e\u3067\u9006\u8ee2\u306eVVV\u304c4\u9023\u52dd|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?96288-95505-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=4 March 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> He scored his fifth goal of the season against [[Roda JC Kerkrade|Roda JC]], but was sent off in the 73rd minutes for an unprofessional foul, in a 3\u20131 loss.<ref>{{cite news|title=Van Veldhoven: \"Wereld ziet er weer anders uit\"|url=https://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbalnieuws/200023/van-veldhoven-wereld-ziet-er-weer-anders-uit/|publisher=FC Update|language=Dutch|date=10 March 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Aanklager wil Yoshida drie wedstrijden schorsen|url=https://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbalnieuws/200208/aanklager-wil-yoshida-drie-wedstrijden-schorsen/|publisher=FC Update|language=Dutch|date=10 March 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> After serving a two match suspension, Yoshida returned to the starting line-up, starting the whole game, in a 2\u20130 loss against PSV Eindhoven on 31 March 2012.<ref>{{cite news|title=Yoshida mist duels met NEC en Heerenveen|url=https://www.fcupdate.nl/voetbalnieuws/200214/yoshida-mist-duels-met-nec-en-heerenveen/|publisher=FC Update|language=Dutch|date=12 March 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u51fa\u5834\u505c\u6b62\u660e\u3051\u306e\u5409\u7530\u304c3\u6226\u3076\u308a\u5148\u767a\u3082\u2026VVV\u306f4\u9023\u6557|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?97394-97149-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Dutch|date=31 March 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> He later started all the four matches in the relegation play\u2013offs and helped the club retain their Eredivisie league status once again.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5409\u7530\u30d5\u30eb\u51fa\u5834\u306eVVV\u3001\u6607\u964d\u683c\u30d7\u30ec\u30fc\u30aa\u30d5\u7b2c1\u6226\u306f2\u90e8\u76f8\u624b\u306b\u30b9\u30b3\u30a2\u30ec\u30b9\u30c9\u30ed\u30fc|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?99262-99902-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=11 May 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u5409\u7530\u30d5\u30eb\u51fa\u5834\u306eVVV\u3001\u58ee\u7d76\u306a\u6253\u3061\u5408\u3044\u5236\u3057\u6607\u964d\u683c\u30d7\u30ec\u30fc\u30aa\u30d5\u6c7a\u52dd\u3078|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?99427-100109-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=14  May 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u5409\u7530\u30d5\u30eb\u51fa\u5834\u306eVVV\u304c\u6575\u5730\u3067\u5148\u52dd\u30011\u90e8\u6b8b\u7559\u306b\u738b\u624b|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?99562-100365-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=17 May 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u5409\u7530\u30d5\u30eb\u51fa\u5834\u306eVVV\u30012\u6226\u5408\u8a084-3\u30671\u90e8\u6b8b\u7559\u6c7a\u3081\u308b|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?99737-100561-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=20 May 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Yoshida\u2019s experience in the relegation play\u2013offs led him to write a blog about the subject.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u300c\u30d7\u30ec\u30fc\u30aa\u30d5\u3063\u3066\u306a\u3093\u3067\u3053\u3093\u306a\u30ad\u30c4\u3044\u306e?\u300d \u6b8b\u7559\u3078\u6b8b\u308a1\u52dd\u306eVVV\u5409\u7530\u304c\u5fc3\u5883\u7db4\u308b|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?99576-100384-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=18 May 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> At the end of the 2011\u201312 season, Yoshida went on to make thirty\u2013seven appearances and scoring five times in all competitions as a central defender.\n\nIn the 2012\u201313 season, Yoshida made two appearances for the side, including one against [[ADO Den Haag]] on 25 August 2012, which he set up the club\u2019s first goal of the game, as they lost 4\u20132 in what turns out to be his last appearance for VVV-Venlo.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5409\u7530\u304c\u30dc\u30e9\u30f3\u30c1\u3067\u9014\u4e2d\u51fa\u5834\u3082\u30df\u30b9\u304b\u3089\u5931\u70b9\u3001VVV\u306f\u30e6\u30c8\u30ec\u30d2\u30c8\u306b\u6557\u308c\u308b|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?103704-105590-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=18 August 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title= VVV\u3067\u306e\u6700\u7d42\u6226?\u5409\u7530\u304c\u5148\u5236\u30a2\u30b7\u30b9\u30c8\u30824\u5931\u70b9\u306e\u9006\u8ee2\u8ca0\u3051|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?104001-105930-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=26 August 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Southampton===\n[[File:Yoshida.jpg|thumb|left|300px|Yoshida playing for [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] in 2017.]]\n\nOn 30 August 2012, Yoshida agreed to join newly\u2013promoted [[Premier League]] side [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] on a three-year contract for a fee thought to be in the region of \u00a33 million and was joined by his teammate, Tadanari Lee.<ref>{{cite web|title=Japan's Yoshida Set For Saints|url=http://www.saintsfc.co.uk/news/article/japans-yoshida-set-for-saints-343281.aspx|publisher=Southampton F.C.|date=30 August 2012|accessdate=30 August 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120901102921/http://www.saintsfc.co.uk/news/article/japans-yoshida-set-for-saints-343281.aspx|archivedate=5 April 2020|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/19426865 |title=Southampton sign Maya Yoshida, Japan's Olympic captain|date=30 August 2012|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=1 September 2012}}</ref> Upon joining the club, he said to a local newspaper [[Southern Daily Echo|Daily Echo]] in an exclusive interview that the move to England will help him grow as a player.<ref name=\"Yoshida Interview1\">{{cite news|title=Maya Yoshida moved to Southampton to grow as a player in the Premier League|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/9934463.maya-yoshida-moved-to-southampton-to-grow-as-a-player-in-the-premier-league/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=18 September 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nYoshida made his debut for the Saints on 15 September 2012, against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in a 6\u20131 defeat, coming on as a 28th-minute substitute for [[Jos Hooiveld]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Arsenal 6\u20131 Southampton|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/19528203|publisher=BBC Sport|date=15 September 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> He then made his home debut a week later on 22 September 2012 in a 4\u20131 win over [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]], playing the whole 90 minutes.<ref>{{cite news|last=Lewis|first=Aimee|title=Southampton 4\u20131 Aston Villa|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/19615244|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=5 April 2020|date=22 September 2012}}</ref> Since joining the club, Yoshida quickly became a first team regular, playing in the centre\u2013back position and forming a partnership with [[Jos\u00e9 Fonte]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Saints' fab four to take centre stage on Merseyside|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/9954466.saints-fab-four-to-take-centre-stage-on-merseyside/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=28 September 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Clyne boost for Saints defence|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/9995548.clyne-boost-for-saints-defence/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=19 October 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Yoshida: Saints can rule Britannia|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/10131042.yoshida-saints-can-rule-britannia/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=29 December 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> During a 1\u20131 draw against [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]] on 10 November 2012, Yoshida made a poor control to the ball that led [[Nathan Dyer]] scoring an equaliser.<ref>{{cite news|title=Southampton 1\u20131 Swansea City|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/20189996|publisher=BBC Sport|date=10 November 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Despite, he continued to retain his first team place against [[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|Queens Park Rangers]] and helped them win 3\u20131 on 15 November 2012.<ref>{{cite news|title=Queens Park Rangers 1\u20133 Southampton|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/20278600|publisher=BBC Sport|date=15 November 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Along the way, he was rotated to playing in the left\u2013back and right\u2013back positions.<ref>{{cite news|title=Adkins urged to Shaw up defence|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/10009574.adkins-urged-to-shaw-up-defence/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=26 October 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Southampton linked to \u00a38m move for Italian defender Davide Astori|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/10132439.southampton-linked-to-8m-move-for-italian-defender-davide-astori/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=31 December 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Boruc save earns Saints point|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/10279353.boruc-save-earns-saints-point/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=9 March 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Since making his debut for Southampton, Yoshida started in every matches for the side and helped improve the results on both the club and the player, himself.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ex-Saint Watson: Adkins needs battlers to complement his creative stars|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/10140225.ex-saint-watson-adkins-needs-battlers-to-complement-his-creative-stars/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=4 January 2013|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Yoshida could be first to book World Cup ticket|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/10312573.yoshida-could-be-first-to-book-world-cup-ticket/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=26 March 2013|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Yoshida dreams of United move|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/10368837.yoshida-dreams-of-united-move/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=26 April 2013|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Having started the 2012\u201313 season at the bottom of the table, results has improved and he helped the side avoid relegation by finishing fourteenth place.<ref>{{cite news|title=Maya's happy shock at Saints recovery|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/10383719.mayas-happy-shock-at-saints-recovery/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=27 April 2013|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Southampton 1\u20131 Stoke City|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/22499096|publisher=BBC Sport|date=14 May 2013|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> In his first season at Southampton, he went on to make thirty\u2013four appearances in all competitions.\n\nHowever at the start of the 2013\u201314 season, Yoshida\u2019s first team opportunities became limited under the management of [[Mauricio Pochettino]] and found himself on the substitute bench.<ref>{{cite news|title=Artur boost for England|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/10661094.artur-boost-for-england/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=6 September 2013|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Osvaldo leads the way for Saints stars|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/10666485.osvaldo-leads-the-way-for-saints-stars/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=10 September 2013|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=COMMENT: Bad night for Saints and their forgotten trio of Cork, Yoshida and Gazzaniga|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/10855810.comment-bad-night-for-saints-and-their-forgotten-trio-of-cork-yoshida-and-gazzaniga/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=4 December 2013|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Despite this, he made his first appearance of the season, in a 5\u20131 win against [[Barnsley F.C.|Barnsley]] on 27 August 2013.<ref>{{cite news|title=Barnsley 1\u20135 Southampton|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/23763998|publisher=BBC Sport|date=27 August 2013|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Yoshida then scored his first goal for Southampton in a 2\u20131 defeat to [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]] in the [[Football League Cup|League Cup]] on 6 November 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/24739094|title=Sunderland 2 \u2013 1 Southampton|publisher=BBC Sport|date=6 November 2013 |accessdate=6 November 2013}}</ref> A month later on 4 December 2013, he made his first Premier League appearance, starting the whole game, in a 3\u20132 loss against [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Southampton 2\u20133 Aston Villa|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/25115885|publisher=BBC Sport|date=4 December 2013|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> At the start of January, Yoshida had a first team run in following an injury of [[Dejan Lovren]], starting the next six matches and improved with the results.<ref>{{cite news|title=Southampton 2\u20132 Arsenal|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/25822287|publisher=BBC Sport|date=28 January 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Fulham 0\u20133 Southampton|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/25892225|publisher=BBC Sport|date=1 February 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Yoshida produces \"faultless\" performance|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/11003202.yoshida-produces-faultless-performance/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=12 February 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Maya never thought to quit 'fantastic' Saints|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/11000502.maya-never-thought-to-quit-fantastic-saints/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=11 February 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> He scored his first Premier League goal in a 3\u20131 defeat at [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] on 22 February 2014 after a [[Steven Davis]] free kick.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hassan|first=Nabil|title=West Ham 3 \u2013 1 Southampton |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/26202718 |publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=21 March 2014|date=22 February 2014}}</ref> But following Lovern\u2019s return, he was once again behind the pecking order in the centre\u2013back competitions, as well as, his own injury concerns.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5409\u7530\u30d9\u30f3\u30c1\u306e\u30b5\u30a6\u30b5\u30f3\u30d7\u30c8\u30f3\u306f\u30af\u30ea\u30b9\u30bf\u30eb\u30fb\u30d1\u30ec\u30b9\u306b\u5b8c\u5c01\u52dd\u5229|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?134281-134281-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=9 March 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u30b5\u30a6\u30b5\u30f3\u30d7\u30c8\u30f3DF\u5409\u7530\u9ebb\u4e5f\u304c\u5168\u6cbb\u7d046\u30017\u9031\u9593\u306e\u8ca0\u50b7\u3001\u6307\u63ee\u5b98\u300cW\u676f\u306f\u9593\u306b\u5408\u3046\u3060\u308d\u3046\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?135395-135395-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=28 March 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Poch wants to beef up small squad|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/11164546.poch-wants-to-beef-up-small-squad/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=23 April 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> At the end of the 2013\u201314 season, Yoshida went on to make fourteen appearances and scoring two times in all competitions.\n\nAt the start of the 2014\u201315 season, Yoshida regained his first team place, playing in the centre\u2013back position, following Lovern\u2019s departure.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ronald Koeman says the arrival of Florin Gardos represents the last centre-half signing of the summer at Southampton|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/11414036.ronald-koeman-says-the-arrival-of-florin-gardos-represents-the-last-centre-half-signing-of-the-summer-at-southampton/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=17 August 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Southampton 0\u20130 West Bromwich Albion|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/28816296|publisher=BBC Sport|date=24 August 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=West Ham United 1\u20133 Southampton|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/28906779|publisher=BBC Sport|date=30 August 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Ronald Koeman hails Southampton's defence|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/11547457.ronald-koeman-hails-southamptons-defence/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=21 October 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> However, during a 1\u20130 win against [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]] on 20 September 2014, he suffered ankle injury that saw him substituted in the second half, resulting in him sidelined for four weeks.<ref>{{cite news|title=Saints manager expects James Ward-Prowse, Maya Yoshida and Toby Alderweireld to make quick returns from injury|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/11486987.saints-manager-expects-james-ward-prowse-maya-yoshida-and-toby-alderweireld-to-make-quick-returns-from-injury/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=21 September 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Swansea City 0\u20131 Southampton|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/29187272|publisher=BBC Sport|date=20 September 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Although Yoshida returned from injury, he was placed on the substitute bench until on 30 November 2014 against [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]], coming on as a second\u2013half substitute, in a 3\u20130 loss.<ref>{{cite news|title=Saints stars benefit from extra days of rest|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/11620792.saints-stars-benefit-from-extra-days-of-rest/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=30 November 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Saints suffer City defeat|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/11635659.saints-suffer-city-defeat/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=30 November 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=COMMENT: Morgan Schneiderlin injury against Manchester City exposes Saints' lack of squad depth compared to Premier League title chasers|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/11635816.comment-morgan-schneiderlin-injury-against-manchester-city-exposes-saints-lack-of-squad-depth-compared-to-premier-league-title-chasers/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=1 December 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> His next goal came on 20 December 2014, in a 3\u20130 victory over [[Everton F.C.|Everton]], with Steven Davis again providing the assist.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Cryer|first1=Andy|title=Southampton 3 \u2013 0 Everton|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/30459790|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=31 December 2014|date=20 December 2014}}</ref> Two weeks later on 8 January 2015, Southampton announced that Yoshida and the club had agreed terms to an extension of his contract until 2018.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lucas|first1=Jim|title=Yoshida extends Saints deal until 2018|url=http://www.saintsfc.co.uk/news/article/20150102-maya-yoshida-contract-2177890.aspx|website=Southampton FC|accessdate=8 January 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150102173933/http://www.saintsfc.co.uk/news/article/20150102-maya-yoshida-contract-2177890.aspx|archivedate=5 April 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> After spending January with Japan\u2019s campaign at the AFC Asian Cup, he returned to the starting line-up and played the whole game, in a 1\u20130 loss against Swansea City on 1 February 2015.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sadio Mane and Maya Yoshida to return for Saints|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/11762900.sadio-mane-and-maya-yoshida-to-return-for-saints/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=31 January 2015|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Southampton 0\u20131 Swansea City|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/30971834|publisher=BBC Sport|date=1 February 2015|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> In a follow\u2013up match against Queens Park Rangers, Yoshida played an important role in the game when he set up the only goal of the game, in a 1\u20130 win.<ref>{{cite news|title=Queens Park Rangers 0\u20131 Southampton|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/31071178|publisher=BBC Sport|date=14 February 2015|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Towards the end of the season, he found himself in and out of the starting line-up in the first team and demoted on the substitute bench.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ronald Koeman says Maya Yoshida can solve Southampton's left-back dilemma|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/11781904.ronald-koeman-says-maya-yoshida-can-solve-southamptons-left-back-dilemma/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=15 February 2015|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9ebb\u4e5f7\u6226\u3076\u308a\u51fa\u5834\u306a\u3057\u306e\u30b5\u30a6\u30b5\u30f3\u30d7\u30c8\u30f3\u306f\u30c1\u30a7\u30eb\u30b7\u30fc\u3068\u5206\u3051\u308b|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?158941-158941-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=16 March 2015|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Southampton 2\u20130 Hull City|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/32179964|publisher=BBC Sport|date=11 April 2015|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Despite this, Yoshida helped the club finished seventh place in the league, resulting in their qualifying for the UEFA Europa League next season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Maya Yoshida believes that he and Southampton are ready to play in Europe|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/12916984.maya-yoshida-believes-that-he-and-southampton-are-ready-to-play-in-europe/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=28 April 2015|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> At the end of the 2014\u201315 season, he went on to make twenty\u2013three appearances and scoring once in all competitions.\n\n[[File:Southampton FC versus FC Augsburg (36304197506).jpg|thumb|right|300px|Yoshida pictured with the young mascots ahead of a friendly match against [[FC Augsburg]] in 2017.]]\n\nAt the start of the 2015\u201316 season, Yoshida started the season well when he helped a clean sheet in both legs by beating [[SBV Vitesse|Vitesse]] 5\u20130 on aggregate in the third round of the UEFA Europa League.<ref>{{cite news|title=Southampton 3\u20130 Vitesse|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/33667103|publisher=BBC Sport|date=30 July 2015|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Vitesse 0\u20131 Southampton|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/33738509|publisher=BBC Sport|date=6 Au