nty\u2013seven appearances and scoring two times in all competitions.\n\nAt the start of the 2016\u201317 season, Yoshida started the match against [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] in the opening game of the season, resulting a 1\u20131 draw.<ref>{{cite news|title=Southampton 1\u20131 Watford|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36994444|publisher=BBC Sport|date=13 August 2016|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> However, he became a backup in the club\u2019s centre\u2013back position behind [[Virgil van Dijk]] and Fonte.<ref>{{cite news|title=Jose Fonte and Cedric Soares could be involved for Southampton against Watford|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/14677279.jose-fonte-and-cedric-soares-could-be-involved-for-southampton-against-watford/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=12 August 2016|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=COMMENT: Claude Puel faces tricky selection dilemma ahead of two important games for Southampton|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/14742017.comment-claude-puel-faces-tricky-selection-dilemma-ahead-of-two-important-games-for-southampton/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=12 September 2016|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Forgotten man Florin Gardos could be set for St Mary's return|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/14875164.forgotten-man-florin-gardos-could-be-set-for-st-marys-return/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=9 November 2016|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Despite this, national newspaper [[Daily Mirror]] mentioned Yoshida in their article of Premier League pace-setters.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u82f1\u306b\u885d\u6483\uff01\u5409\u7530\u9ebb\u4e5f\u306e\u8db3\u306e\u901f\u3055\u304c\u30a6\u30a9\u30eb\u30b3\u30c3\u30c8\u3068\u540c\u3058|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/world/news/1720579.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=6 October 2016|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Maya Yoshida is as quick as Theo Walcott - 7 shock discoveries from the list of Premier League pace-sett