nce, saying he was \"fantastic\" and mentioned that he could be a \"a captain\" for Southampton.<ref>{{cite news|title=Claude Puel hails Yoshida - and talks about Martin Caceres' potential debut|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/15208775.claude-puel-hails-yoshida-and-talks-about-martin-caceres-potential-debut/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=7 April 2017|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> In a follow\u2013up, Yoshida captained the side once again, in a 1\u20130 win against [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]].<ref>{{cite news|title=West Bromwich Albion 0\u20131 Southampton|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/39464041|publisher=BBC Sport|date=8 April 2017|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> He then made his 100th appearance for Southampton and Premier League overall, becoming the first Japanese player to reach the milestone, in a 0\u20130 draw against Hull City on 29 April 2017.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u30d7\u30ec\u30df\u30a25\u5e74\u76ee\u3067\u9054\u6210\u2026100\u8a66\u5408\u51fa\u5834\u306e\u5409\u7530\u9ebb\u4e5f\u300c\u65e5\u672c\u30b5\u30c3\u30ab\u30fc\u754c\u306b\u3068\u3063\u3066\u5927\u304d\u306a\u4e00\u6b69\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?215027-215027-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=30 April 2017|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u65e5\u672c\u4eba\u521d\u306e\u30d7\u30ec\u30df\u30a2100\u8a66\u5408\u51fa\u5834\u306e\u9ebb\u4e5f\u300c\u3068\u306b\u304b\u304f\u611f\u8b1d\u3057\u304b\u306a\u3044\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?215139-215139-fl |publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=30 April 2017|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> At the end of the 2016\u201317 season, which saw the club finished seventh place, Yoshida went on to make thirty\u2013seven appearances and scoring two times in all competitions.\n\nIn the 2017\u201318 season, Yoshida appeared in the first three league matches of the season, including winning a penalty and it was successfully converted by Austin, in a 3\u20132 win against West Ham United on 19 August 2017.<ref>{{cite news|title=Steven Davis has opened the door for Virgil van Dijk to return to the Saints fold amid his ongoing transfer saga|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/15470307.steven-davis-has-opened-the-door-for-virgil-van-dijk-to-return-to-the-saints-fold-amid-his-ongoing-transfer-saga/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=14 August 2017|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Southampton 3\u20132 West Ham United|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40908330|publisher=BBC Sport|date=19 August 2017|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Virgil van Dijk will have to \"fight\" for his place in the Saints team if he stays beyond the end of the transfer window, according to Steven Davis|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/15498059.virgil-van-dijk-will-have-to-fight-for-his-place-in-the-saints-team-if-he-stays-beyond-the-end-of-the-transfer-window-according-to-steven-davis/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=28 August 2017|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> It was announced on 24 August 2017 that Yoshida signed a further extension of his contract with Southampton until 2020.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Media|first1=SFC|title=Yoshida signs new Saints deal|url=https://southamptonfc.com/news/2017-08-24/maya-yoshida-new-southampton-three-year-contract-announcement|website=Southampton F.C.|accessdate=21 April 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170906072414/https://southamptonfc.com/news/2017-08-24/maya-yoshida-new-southampton-three-year-contract-announcement|archivedate=5 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> He continued to remain in competitions among the centre\u2013backs, which saw him placed on the substitute bench.<ref>{{cite news|title=Wesley Hoedt talks about potential partnership with fellow Netherlands international Virgil van Dijk at Saints|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/15530372.wesley-hoedt-talks-about-potential-partnership-with-fellow-netherlands-international-virgil-van-dijk-at-saints/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=13 September 2017|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Maya Yoshida knows Saints' centre-backs will feel pressure of Virgil van Dijk's return|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/15540694.maya-yoshida-knows-saints-centre-backs-will-feel-pressure-of-virgil-van-dijks-return/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=18 September 2017|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Mauricio Pellegrino has considered a change of formation at Saints - could he finally implement it after the international break?|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/15581154.mauricio-pellegrino-has-considered-a-change-of-formation-at-saints-could-he-finally-implement-it-after-the-international-break/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=7 October 2017|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 30 September 2017 when Yoshida scored his first goal of the season, scoring from a volley in the 75th minutes in a 2\u20131 loss against Stoke City.<ref>{{cite news|title=Stoke City 2\u20131 Southampton|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/41370358|publisher=BBC Sport|date=30 September 2017|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> By the end of 2017, he captained six out of the eight matches for the side.<ref>{{cite news|title=Southampton 1\u20131 Arsenal|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42212590|publisher=BBC Sport|date=10 December 2017|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Manchester United 0\u20130 Southampton|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42411000|publisher=BBC Sport|date=30 December 2017|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Southampton 1\u20132 Crystal Palace|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42411056|publisher=BBC Sport|date=2 January 2018|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Yoshida also scored his second goal of the season, in a 4\u20131 loss against [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] on 13 December 2017.<ref>{{cite news|title=Southampton 1\u20134 Leicester City|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42247116|publisher=BBC Sport|date=13 December 2017|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> However, Yoshida suffered a hamstring injury that kept him out for two weeks.<ref>{{cite news|title=Southampton manager Mauricio Pellegrino defends his tactics after 2-2 draw with Watford|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/15826714.southampton-manager-mauricio-pellegrino-defends-his-tactics-after-2-2-draw-with-watford/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=14 April 2018|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 27 January 2018 when he made return from injury, coming on as a 67th minutes substitute, in a 1\u20130 win against Watford.<ref>{{cite news|title=Southampton 1\u20130 Watford|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42756109|publisher=BBC Sport|date=27 January 2018|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Yoshida\u2019s return was short\u2013lived when he suffered a knee injury that kept him out for two months.<ref>{{cite news|title=Southampton defender Maya Yoshida out for at least a month with a knee injury|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/16041398.southampton-defender-maya-yoshida-out-for-at-least-a-month-with-a-knee-injury/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=22 February 2018|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Maya Yoshida gets ready to fight for his Southampton place|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/16119839.maya-yoshida-gets-ready-to-fight-for-his-southampton-place/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=28 March 2018|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 8 April 2018 when Yoshida returned to the starting line-up and played for 72 minutes before being substituted, in a 3\u20132 loss against Arsenal.<ref>{{cite news|title=Arsenal 3\u20132 Southampton|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/43609100|publisher=BBC Sport|date=8 April 2018|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Throughout the 2017\u201318 season, the club have found themselves in a relegation zone, putting their Premier League status under threat.<ref>{{cite news|title=Southampton's Maya Yoshida says every player must \"take responsibility\"|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/15791772.southamptons-maya-yoshida-says-every-player-must-take-responsibility/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=25 September 2017|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Southampton are in a 'do-or-die' position, says Yoshida|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/16134748.southampton-are-in-a-do-or-die-position-says-yoshida/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=4 April 2018|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> However, in the penultimate match of the season, a 1\u20131 draw with Everton on 5 May 2018, he was sent\u2013off for a second bookable offence, so was suspended for the visit to Swansea City from which Southampton needed a win to survive at their hosts' expense.<ref>{{cite news|title=Everton 1\u20131 Southampton|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/43931930|publisher=BBC Sport|date=5 May 2018|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> The match was won by Southampton, so Swansea City were relegated.<ref>{{cite news|title=Swansea City 0\u20131 Southampton|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/43353971|publisher=BBC Sport|date=8 May 2018|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> At the end of the 2017\u201318 season, Yoshida went on to make twenty\u2013eight appearances and scoring two times in all competitions.\n\nAhead of the 2018\u201319 season, Yoshida was linked a move away from Southampton, with Saudi Arabian side [[Al Hilal SFC|Al Hilal]] interested.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u4e2d\u6771\u79fb\u7c4d\u5831\u9053\u306e\u5409\u7530\u9ebb\u4e5f\u3001\u3084\u306f\u308a\u30b5\u30a6\u30b5\u30f3\u30d7\u30c8\u30f3\u6b8b\u7559\u304b\u2026\u5730\u5143\u7d19\u5831\u9053|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?245383-245383-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=22 May 2018|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> But the transfer speculation came to an end after Yoshida announced his intention to stay at the club.<ref>{{cite news|title=Maya Yoshida's future is decided|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/16238218.maya-yoshidas-future-is-decided/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=21 May 2018|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> At the start of the season, he found his first team opportunities limited under the management of [[Mark Hughes]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Lawrie McMenemy on Southampton's win over Brighton & Hove Albion|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/16608293.lawrie-mcmenemy-on-southamptons-win-over-brighton/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=1 September 2018|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u30b5\u30a6\u30b5\u30f3\u30d7\u30c8\u30f3\u30d5\u30a1\u30f3\u306f\u5409\u7530\u9ebb\u4e5f\u306e\u51fa\u5834\u3092\u71b1\u671b\u2026\u300c\u306a\u305c\u30ad\u30e3\u30d7\u30c6\u30f3\u3088\u308a\u30d5\u30fc\u30c8\u306a\u3093\u3060?\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?255029-255029-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|date=23 September 2018|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u30b5\u30a6\u30b5\u30f3\u30d7\u30c8\u30f3\u5c02\u9580\u30e1\u30c7\u30a3\u30a2\u304c\u5409\u7530\u9ebb\u4e5f\u306e\u8d77\u7528\u3092\u63d0\u8a00\u300c\u30d9\u30b9\u30c6\u30eb\u30b4\u30fc\u30a2\u306e\u30d1\u30fc\u30c8\u30ca\u30fc\u306b\u3075\u3055\u308f\u3057\u3044\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?255331-255331-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=27 September 2018|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 27 August 2018 when Yoshida made his first appearance of the season, starting the whole game, in a 1\u20130 win against [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] in the second round of the EFL Cup.<ref>{{cite news|title=Brighton & Hove Albion 0\u20131 Southampton|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45254464|publisher=BBC Sport|date=28 August 2018|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> He soon had a first team run, starting a lot of matches by the end of 2018.<ref>{{cite news|title=How Southampton players rated against Watford|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/17217295.how-southampton-players-rated-against-watford/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=12 November 2018|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Southampton defender Maya Yoshida chasing another cup run|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/17256170.southampton-defender-maya-yoshida-chasing-another-cup-run/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=26 November 2018|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Southampton manager Ralph Hasenhuttl has a defensive dilemma ahead of Arsenal|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/17293248.southampton-manager-ralph-hasenhuttl-has-a-defensive-dilemma-ahead-of-arsenal/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=13 December 2018|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Following his international commitment with Japan at the AFC Asian Cup came to an end, it wasn\u2019t until on 27 February 2019 when Yoshida returned to the starting line-up and helped the side kept a clean sheet, in a 2\u20130 win against Fulham.<ref>{{cite news|title=Saints 1 Cardiff City 2: Southampton suffer injury-time heartbreak|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/17421468.saints-1-cardiff-city-2-southampton-suffer-injury-time-heartbreak/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=9 February 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Southampton out of the relegation zone after 2-0 win over Fulham|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/17464433.southampton-out-of-the-relegation-zone-after-2-0-win-over-fulham/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=27 February 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Since returning to the first team, he regained his place for the rest of the season and helped Southampton avoid relegation once again.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ralph Hasenhuttl's started better than Mauricio Pochettino|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/17481709.ralph-hasenhuttls-started-better-than-mauricio-pochettino/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=7 March 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=THE VERDICT: The final word on Southampton's 3-1 defeat to Newcastle|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/17588291.the-verdict-the-final-word-on-southamptons-3-1-defeat-to-newcastle/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=22 April 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Southampton defender Maya Yoshida outlines target for safety|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/17581352.southampton-defender-maya-yoshida-outlines-target-for-safety/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=18 April 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Despite being sidelined with an illness that eventually saw him out for the rest of the 2018\u201319 season, Yoshida went on to make twenty appearances in all competitions.<ref>{{cite news|title=Southampton defender Maya Yoshida won't be risked for Huddersfield finale|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/17632223.southampton-defender-maya-yoshida-wont-be-risked-for-huddersfield-finale/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=10 May 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn the 2019\u201320 season, Yoshida made his first appearance of the season, starting the whole game, in a 2\u20131 loss against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] on 17 August 2019.<ref>{{cite news|title=Southampton 1-2 Liverpool|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49302580|publisher=BBC Sport|date=17 August 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> He soon had a first team run ins for the next two months.<ref>{{cite news|title=Southampton defender Maya Yoshida discusses Chelsea|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/17936972.southampton-defender-maya-yoshida-discusses-chelsea/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=1 October 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Sheffield United 0-1 Southampton|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49617983|publisher=BBC Sport|date=14 September 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Wolverhampton Wanderers 1-1 Southampton|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/50024400|publisher=BBC Sport|date=19 October 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Following a [[Southampton F.C. 0\u20139 Leicester City F.C.|9\u20130]] loss to Leicester City, Yoshida was dropped to the substitute bench and never played for the team again.<ref>{{cite news|title=Maya Yoshida believes it's a good time for Southampton to hit reset|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/18052024.maya-yoshida-believes-good-time-southampton-hit-reset/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=23 November 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Maya Yoshida: No one saw my Southampton exit coming|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/18226699.maya-yoshida-no-one-say-southampton-exit-coming/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=11 February 2020|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> By the time he departed the club, Yoshida made eleven appearance this season.\n\n==== Loan to Sampdoria ====\nOn 31 January 2020, Yoshida joined [[Serie A]] side [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]] on loan until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite web|title=Yoshida joins Sampdoria on loan|url=https://www.southamptonfc.com/news/2020-01-31/announcement-maya-yoshida-southampton-sampdoria-loan-deal|publisher=Southampton F.C.|accessdate=1 February 2020|date=31 January 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131202549/https://www.southamptonfc.com/news/2020-01-31/announcement-maya-yoshida-southampton-sampdoria-loan-deal|archivedate=5 April 2020|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|title=Yoshida joins from Southampton|url=https://www.sampdoria.it/en/yoshida-joins-from-southampton/|publisher=Sampdoria|accessdate=1 February 2020|date=31 January 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131232521/https://www.sampdoria.it/en/yoshida-joins-from-southampton/|archivedate=5 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Local newspaper Daily Echo described Yoshida\u2019s departure as \"end of era\".<ref>{{cite news|title=Maya Yoshida has left Southampton to join Sampdoria|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/18202922.southampton-defender-maya-yoshida-set-join-sampdoria/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=31 January 2020|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nHaving appeared on the substitute bench for two matches, Yoshida made his Sampdoria debut against [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Hellas Verona]] on 8 March 2020 and started the whole game, as the club won 2\u20131.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5409\u7530\u9ebb\u4e5f\u306f\u30d9\u30f3\u30c1\u5165\u308a\u3082\u51fa\u756a\u306a\u3057\u3001\u30b5\u30f3\u30d7\u30c9\u30ea\u30a2\u304c\u30c8\u30ea\u30ce\u6483\u7834\u30674\u6226\u3076\u308a\u767d\u661f|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?297479-297479-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=9 February 2020|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u300c\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u306e\u6e96\u5099\u306f\u3067\u304d\u3066\u3044\u308b\u300d\u5409\u7530\u9ebb\u4e5f\u3001\u30bb\u30ea\u30a8A\u3067\u201cDF\u3068\u3057\u3066\u6ce8\u610f\u3059\u3079\u304d\u201d\u3053\u3068\u3068\u306f\u2026|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?298195-298195-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=19 February 2020|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title= Quagliarella ribalta il Verona e tiene la Sampdoria in zona A|url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/08-03-2020/quagliarella-ribalta-verona-tiene-sampdoria-zona-a-3601551803092.shtml|publisher=La Gazzetta Dello Sport|language=Italian|date=8 March 2020|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\n\n[[File:JPN-TUR 20190109 Asian Cup 6.jpg|thumb|left|300px|Yoshida and Turkmen player [[Arslanmyrat Amanow]] at [[2019 Asian Cup]].]]\n\n===Youth career===\n\nYoshida earned a call-up for Japan's U-23 team in April 2008 for the first time following good performance at Nagayo Grampus.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u597d\u8abf\u30fb\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u306e19\u6b73\u3001DF\u5409\u7530\u304cU-23\u4ee3\u8868\u521d\u62db\u96c6|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?36158-16846-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=19 April 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite web|publisher=Sports Reference|title=Maya Yoshida Biography and Statistics|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/yo/maya-yoshida-1.html|accessdate=25 July 2009}}</ref> A month later on 22 May 2008, he made his Japan U23 debut in the [[2008 Toulon Tournament|Toulon Tournament]] and started the whole game, in a 2\u20131 win against [[France national football team|France]].<ref>{{cite news|title=U-23\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u306e\u5409\u7530\u3001\u7a7a\u4e2d\u6226\u3067\u5f37\u3055\u767a\u63ee|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?37671-18397-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=22 May 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Yoshida went on to make two appearances in the tournament, as Japan U-23 finished fourth place after reaching the semi\u2013finals.<ref>{{cite news|title=U-23\u4ee3\u8868\u306f4\u4f4d\u7d42\u6226\u3082\u5b9f\u308a\u591a\u3044\u5927\u4f1a\u306b|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?37912-18673-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=30 May 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nIt was announced on 14 July 2008 that Yoshida was called up to the Japan U-23 team for the [[2008 Summer Olympic]] in Beijing.<ref>{{cite news|title=[\u901f\u5831]\u5317\u4eac\u4e94\u8f2a\u30e1\u30f3\u30d0\u30fc\u767a\u8868|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?39697-20525-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=14 July 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> After appearing twice as an unused substitute, he made his debut in the tournament, starting the whole game, in a 1\u20130 loss against [[Netherlands national under-21 football team|Netherlands]] on 13 August 2008 and the side was eliminated from the tournament.<ref>{{cite news|title=[\u4e94\u8f2a]\u65e5\u672cvs.\u7c73\u56fd \u30b9\u30bf\u30e1\u30f3\u767a\u8868|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?40688-21069-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=8 August 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=[\u4e94\u8f2a]\u65e5\u672cvs\u30ca\u30a4\u30b8\u30a7\u30ea\u30a2 \u30b9\u30bf\u30e1\u30f3\u767a\u8868|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?40817-21691-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=10 August 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=[\u4e94\u8f2a]\u53cd\u753a\u30b8\u30e3\u30d1\u30f3\u306f3\u9023\u6557\u3001\u610f\u5730\u898b\u305b\u3089\u308c\u305a|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?40969-21839-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=13 August 2008|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Four years later, Yoshida was called up to the Japan U-23 team for the second time ahead of the [[2012 Summer Olympics]] in London.<ref>{{cite news|title=ja:\uff35\u2212\uff12\uff13\u65e5\u672c\u4ee3\u8868\u30e1\u30f3\u30d0\u30fc\u9078\u8003\u306b\u898b\u3089\u308c\u305f\uff12\u3064\u306e\u7279\u5fb4 \u30ed\u30f3\u30c9\u30f3\u4e94\u8f2a\u3067\u306e\u6226\u3044\u65b9\u306b\u5909\u5316\u306f\u3042\u308b\u306e\u304b|url=https://sports.yahoo.co.jp/column/detail/201207030003-spnavi|publisher=Sports Navi|language=Japanese|date=3 July 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Ahead of the tournament, he was named as captain by Manager [[Takashi Sekizuka]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u4e3b\u5c06\u306fOA\u67a0\u306e\u5409\u7530\u3000\u4e94\u8f2a\u30b5\u30c3\u30ab\u30fc\u65e5\u672c\u7537\u5b50|url=https://www.nikkei.com/article/DGXNSSXKA0439_S2A720C1000000/|publisher=Nikkei|language=Japanese|date=22 July 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Yoshida\u2019s first match as captain came on 26 July 2012 against [[Spain national under-23 football team|Spain]] and helped the side kept a clean, in a 1\u20130 win.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u3010\u30b9\u30da\u30a4\u30f3\u3011\u73fe\u5730\u30e1\u30c7\u30a3\u30a2\u304c\u5831\u3058\u305f\u300c\u4e94\u8f2a\u4ee3\u8868\u3001\u65e5\u672c\u306b\u6557\u5317\u300d|url=https://sportiva.shueisha.co.jp/clm/football/wfootball/2012/07/27/post_142/|publisher=Sporiva Shueisha|language=Japanese|date=27 July 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> In the next two matches, he helped the side kept two more clean sheets against [[Morocco national under-23 football team|Morocco U23]] and [[Honduras national under-23 football team|Honduras U23]] with a win and draw respectively, resulting in Japan U23 qualifying for the knockout stage.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u6c38\u4e95\u304c\u5287\u7684V\u5f3e!!U-23\u65e5\u672c\u4ee3\u8868\u304c\u9023\u52dd\u30673\u5927\u4f1a\u3076\u308a\u306e\u30d9\u30b9\u30c88\u9032\u51fa\u6c7a\u5b9a|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?102804-104552-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=30 July 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=U\uff0d23\u65e5\u672c\u4ee3\u8868\u3001\u30db\u30f3\u30b8\u30e5\u30e9\u30b9\u306b\u5f15\u304d\u5206\u3051\u3067\u4e88\u9078\u7121\u6557\u306e1\u4f4d\u3067\u7a81\u7834\uff0f\u30ed\u30f3\u30c9\u30f3\u4e94\u8f2a|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20120802/63815.html|publisher=Soccer King|language=Japanese|date=2 August 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Yoshida scored his first goal of the tournament, scoring a header from [[Hiroshi Kiyotake]]\u2019s free kick, in a 3\u20130 against [[Egypt national under-23 football team|Egypt U23]] in the quarter\u2013finals.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u6c38\u4e95!\u5409\u7530!\u5927\u6d25!U-23\u4ee3\u8868\u304c3\u767a\u5b8c\u5c01\u306744\u5e74\u3076\u308a\u306e\u30d9\u30b9\u30c84\u9032\u51fa\u6c7a\u5b9a|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?103087-104872-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=4 August 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> However, he continued to lead Japan U23 finished fourth place in the Olympics after losing to [[Mexico national under-23 football team|Mexico U23]] and [[South Korea national under-23 football team|South Korea U23]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u521d\u306e\u6c7a\u52dd\u306a\u3089\u305a\u2026U-23\u4ee3\u8868\u306f\u30e1\u30ad\u30b7\u30b3\u306b\u9006\u8ee2\u8ca0\u3051\u30673\u4f4d\u6c7a\u5b9a\u6226\u3078|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?103250-105056-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=8 August 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u4e3b\u5c06\u3068\u3057\u3066\u5c0e\u3044\u305f4\u5f37\u3001\u5409\u7530\u300c\u30aa\u30fc\u30d0\u30fc\u30a8\u30a4\u30b8\u3092\u5f15\u304d\u53d7\u3051\u3066\u3088\u304b\u3063\u305f\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?103384-105205-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=11 August 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> After the match, Yoshida said: \"I can appreciate that the team whose initial expectation was not so high has advanced to the top four for the first time in 44 years. I do not think why I could not go on it or got a medal The Olympics are a gathering of young athletes called the U-23, and it is important that as many athletes go into the national team as A and stand on the World Cup stage.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=4\u4f4d\u3092\u6094\u3057\u304c\u308bDF\u5409\u7530\u300c\u97d3\u56fd\u306b\u306f\u4e8c\u5ea6\u3068\u8ca0\u3051\u305f\u304f\u306a\u3044\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?103474-105317-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=12 August 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Senior career===\n\n[[File:Brazil-Japan, Confederations Cup 2013 (12).jpg|thumb|right|300px|Yoshida and [[Neymar]] clashing for a ball during an opening match of the [[2013 FIFA Confederations Cup|2013 Confederations Cup]] between [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] and [[Japan national football team|Japan]].]]\n\nIn December 2009, Yoshida was called up to the [[Japan national football team|senior national team]] for the first time.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5e73\u5747\u5e74\u9f6220.95\u6b73\u306e\u82e5\u304dA\u4ee3\u8868\u3001\u30a4\u30a8\u30e1\u30f3\u6226\u306e\u5148\u767a\u30e1\u30f3\u30d0\u30fc\u306f?|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?63317-48112-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=21 December 2009|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> He made his full international debut for [[Japan national football team|Japan]] on 6 January 2010 in a [[2011 AFC Asian Cup]] qualifier against [[Yemen national football team|Yemen]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5e73\u5c71\u304c\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u6226\u3067\u30cf\u30c3\u30c8!!\u82e5\u304dA\u4ee3\u8868\u304c\u9bae\u3084\u304b\u9006\u8ee2\u52dd\u3061|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?63959-49013-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=6 January 2010|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Yoshida later reflected on his debut, saying: \"Of course Yemen war of 2010 (3-2) because it was all the way to the target, I was happy.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5409\u7530\u9ebb\u4e5f\u72ec\u5360\u30a4\u30f3\u30bf\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u300c\u7f6e\u304b\u308c\u3066\u3044\u308b\u72b6\u6cc1\u3067\u30d9\u30b9\u30c8\u3092\u51fa\u3057\u7d9a\u3051\u308b\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?139260-139260-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=19 May 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> After fracturing his fingers, Yoshida stated that he was determined to recovery from his injury and hope to get called up for the [[2010 FIFA World Cup|2010 World Cup]] squad.<ref>{{cite news|title=VVV\u5409\u7530\u300cW\u676f\u3042\u304d\u3089\u3081\u306a\u3044\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?68325-55336-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=5 March 2010|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> However, Yoshida did not make the cut. <ref>{{cite news |script-title=ja:\u30d5\u30a1\u30f3\u304c\u9078\u3093\u3060\u65e5\u672c\u4ee3\u8868\uff12\uff13\u4eba\u3000\uff26\uff37\u306f\u610f\u5916\u306a\u7d50\u679c\u306b\u2026 |url=http://www.sponichi.co.jp/soccer/news/2010/05/09/kiji/K20100509Z00000030.html|publisher=Sponichi Annex|language=Japanese|date=9 May 2010|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2010, Yoshida was called up for the [[2011 AFC Asian Cup]] in [[Qatar]].<ref>{{cite news|title=[\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u676f\u30e1\u30f3\u30d0\u30fc\u767a\u8868]\u674e\u304c\u521d\u9078\u51fa\u3001\u5409\u7530\u3001\u67cf\u6728\u3089\u3082\u5fa9\u5e30|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?78267-69730-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=24 December 2010|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Under the management of [[Alberto Zaccheroni]], it\u2019s emerged that Yoshida is expecting to start in the centre\u2013back position ahead of the tournament.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u602a\u6211\u4eba\u7d9a\u51fa\u3067DF\u30e9\u30a4\u30f3\u518d\u7de8\u3078\u3002\u30c1\u30e3\u30f3\u30b9\u3064\u304b\u3080\u306e\u306f\u69d9\u91ce?\u4f0a\u91ce\u6ce2? \u305d\u308c\u3068\u3082\u5409\u7530?|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?78291-69753-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=24 December 2010|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u6545\u969c\u8005\u7d9a\u51fa\u306e\u30d4\u30f3\u30c1\u3082\u30c1\u30e3\u30f3\u30b9\u306b\u3001\u65b022\u756a\u30fb\u5409\u7530\u304c\u5b58\u5728\u611f|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?78937-70654-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=8 January 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=2\u65e5\u9023\u7d9a\u3067\u4e00\u90e8\u975e\u516c\u958b\u3002CB\u5148\u767a\u306b\u5409\u7530\u304c\u6d6e\u4e0a|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?78868-70567-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=6 January 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> He scored his first Japan goal, in a 1\u20131 draw against [[Jordan national football team|Jordan]] on 9 January 2011.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u30ed\u30b9\u30bf\u30a4\u30e0\u540c\u70b9\u3000\u5409\u7530\u304c\u6551\u3063\u305f\uff0f\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u676f|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/asiancup/2011/news/p-sc-tp2-20110110-722813.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=10 January 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Yoshida started two more matches in the group-stage, as Japan progressed through the knockout stage.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5409\u7530\uff21\uff2b\uff22\u306b\u8ca0\u3051\u305f\u304c\u30b7\u30ea\u30a2\u306b\u306f\u52dd\u3064|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/asiancup/2011/news/p-sc-tp2-20110113-723932.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=13 January 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u5ddd\u5cf6\u4ee3\u5f79\u306e\u897f\u5ddd\u304c\u30b7\u30e3\u30c3\u30c8\u30a2\u30a6\u30c8\u3001\u201c\u4e88\u884c\u7df4\u7fd2\u201d\u3082\u517c\u306d\u305f\u5b8c\u5c01\u5287|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?79415-71276-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=18 January 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> However, Yoshida was sent\u2013off for a second bookable offence, in a 3\u20132 win against [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]] in the quarter\u2013finals of the AFC Asian Cup.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9999\u5ddd2\u767a!\u4f0a\u91ce\u6ce2\u5287\u5f3e!\u30b6\u30c3\u30af\u30b8\u30e3\u30d1\u30f3\u304c10\u4eba\u3067\u5730\u5143\u30ab\u30bf\u30fc\u30eb\u306b\u9006\u8ee2\u52dd\u5229|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?79595-71538-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=21 January 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> After serving a one match suspension, Yoshida returned to the starting line-ups in the [[2011 AFC Asian Cup Final|AFC Asian Cup Final]] against [[Australia national football team|Australia]] and played 120 minutes, as they beat the Socceroos 1\u20130 to win the AFC Asian Cup, thanks to [[Tadanari Lee]].<ref>{{cite news|title=PK\u6226\u306e\u6b7b\u95d8\u5236\u3059!!\u30b6\u30c3\u30af\u30b8\u30e3\u30d1\u30f3\u304c\u5bbf\u6575\u30fb\u97d3\u56fd\u3092\u4e0b\u30572\u5927\u4f1a\u3076\u308a\u6c7a\u52dd\u3078|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?79764-71767-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=26 January 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=2\u5927\u4f1a\u3076\u308a\u6700\u591a4\u5ea6\u76ee\u306e\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u5236\u8987!\u9014\u4e2d\u51fa\u5834\u30fb\u674e\u306e\u5287\u5f3e\u3067\u5ef6\u9577\u6226\u5236\u3059|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?79959-72010-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=29 January 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Between 7 June 2011 and 2 September 2011, Yoshida kept three consecutive three cleans; including once against [[North Korea national football team|North Korea]], which he scored the only goal of the game. <ref>{{cite news|title=3-4-3\u309290\u5206\u9593\u8cab\u304f\u3082\u9060\u3044\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u2026\u30b6\u30c3\u30af\u30b8\u30e3\u30d1\u30f3\u306f2\u6226\u9023\u7d9a\u30b9\u30b3\u30a2\u30ec\u30b9\u30c9\u30ed\u30fc|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?85685-80048-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=7 June 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9999\u5ddd\u3001\u5fa9\u6d3b2\u767a!\u30b6\u30c3\u30af\u30b8\u30e3\u30d1\u30f3\u304c\u97d3\u56fd\u304b\u308937\u5e74\u3076\u308a3\u5f97\u70b9\u3067\u6b74\u53f2\u7684\u5927\u52dd|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?88671-84014-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=10 August 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u65e5\u672c-\u5317\u671d\u9bae\u306f0-0\u3067\u5f8c\u534a\u3078|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?89709-85388-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=2 September 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Yoshida kept an additional three more clean sheets between 7 October 2011 and 11 November 2011.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u65e5\u672c\uff0d\u30d9\u30c8\u30ca\u30e0\u6226\u3000\u8a66\u5408\u8a73\u7d30\uff0f\u89aa\u5584\u8a66\u5408|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/f-sc-tp2-20111007-846263.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=7 October 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u65e5\u672c\uff18\uff0d\uff10\u30bf\u30b8\u30af\u3000\u8a66\u5408\u8a73\u7d30\uff0f\uff37\u676f\u4e88\u9078|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/f-sc-tp2-20111011-848332.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=11 October 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u65e5\u672c\u30014-0\u3067\u30bf\u30b8\u30ad\u30b9\u30bf\u30f3\u4e0b\u3059\u3000W\u676f\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u4e88\u9078|url=https://www.nikkei.com/article/DGXNASDH11038_R11C11A1000001/|publisher=Nikkei Website|language=Japanese|date=11 November 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the Olympics, Yoshida continued to help Japan by keeping three consecutive clean sheets between 6 September 2012 and 12 October 2012 against [[United Arab Emirates national football team|UAE]], [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]] and [[France national football team|France]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u30a4\u30e9\u30af\u6226\u3078\u9078\u624b\u3092\u898b\u6975\u3081\u308b\u30b6\u30c3\u30af\u3001\u300c11\u4eba\u4e2d\u30018\u4eba\u304b\u30899\u4eba\u306f\u982d\u306e\u4e2d\u306b\u3042\u308b\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?104509-106544-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=6 September 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u524d\u7530\u306e\u6c7a\u52dd\u30d8\u30c3\u30c9\u3067\u30a4\u30e9\u30af\u306b\u52dd\u5229\u3001\u30db\u30fc\u30e03\u9023\u52dd\u3067\u30d6\u30e9\u30b8\u30ebW\u676f\u3078\u524d\u9032|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?104699-106761-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=11 September 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9999\u5ddd\u304c\u5287\u7684\u6c7a\u52dd\u5f3e!!\u65e5\u672c\u304c\u30b5\u30f3\u30c9\u30cb\u3067\u30d5\u30e9\u30f3\u30b9\u3092\u4e0b\u3057\u521d\u52dd\u5229|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?106106-108226-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=12 October 2012|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> He later helped Japan qualify for the World Cup after drawing 1\u20131 against Australia on 4 June 2013.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u672c\u7530\u304c\u30ed\u30b9\u30bf\u30a4\u30e0\u306b\u540c\u70b9PK!!\u4e16\u754c\u6700\u901f\u30675\u5927\u4f1a\u9023\u7d9a\u306eW\u676f\u51fa\u5834\u6c7a\u5b9a|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?115582-119800-fl|publisher=Web Gekisak|language=Japanese|date=4 June 2013|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Two days later, Yoshida was called up to the national side for the [[2013 FIFA Confederations Cup|2013 Confederations Cup]] squad.<ref>{{cite news|script-title=ja:\u3082\u3057\u4e00\u4eba\u8db3\u305b\u308b\u3068\u3057\u305f\u3089\u3001\u65e5\u672c\u4ee3\u8868\u306b\u8ab0\u3092\u9078\u3076\uff1f|url=https://www.footballchannel.jp/2013/06/06/post5164/|publisher=Football Channel Website|language=Japanese|date=6 June 2013|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> He was featured three times in the tournament, as Japan loss all three matches and was eliminated in the Group Stage.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u51b7\u9759\u306b\u6557\u6226\u53d7\u3051\u6b62\u3081\u308b\u5185\u7530\u3001\u30cd\u30a4\u30de\u30fc\u30eb\u306b\u3064\u3044\u3066\u306f\u300c\u3055\u3059\u304c\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?116055-120358-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=16 June 2013|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u30a4\u30bf\u30ea\u30a2\u3068\u58ee\u7d76\u306a\u6253\u3061\u5408\u3044\u3082\u60dc\u6557\u2026\u65e5\u672c\u306f\u9023\u6557\u3067GL\u6557\u9000\u6c7a\u5b9a|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?116198-120530-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=20 June 2013|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u30bb\u30c3\u30c8\u30d7\u30ec\u30fc\u306e\u5931\u70b9\u3092\u6094\u3084\u3080\u9ebb\u4e5f\u30013\u62269\u5931\u70b9\u306b\u300c\u3075\u304c\u3044\u306a\u3044\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?116352-120712-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=22 June 2013|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Maya Yoshida 2018.jpg|thumb|left|300px|Yoshida playing for Japan during a match against [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] in the round of 16 of the [[2018 FIFA World Cup|FIFA World Cup]].]]\n\nIn May 2014, Yoshida was named in Japan's preliminary squad for the [[2014 FIFA World Cup|2014 World Cup]] in Brazil.<ref>{{cite news|script-title=ja:\u65e5\u672c\u306e\uff37\u676f\u4e88\u5099\u767b\u9332\u9078\u624b\u3092\u30d5\u30e9\u30a4\u30f3\u30b0\u767a\u8868|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/brazil2014/news/p-sc-tp0-20140510-1298516.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=10 May 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> In the end, he made it to the final cut for the 23 man squad.<ref>{{cite news|script-title=ja:\u5927\u4e45\u4fdd\u3001\u658e\u85e4\u3089\u9078\u51fa\u3000\uff37\u676f\u30e1\u30f3\u30d0\u30fc\u4e00\u89a7|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/brazil2014/news/f-sc-tp0-20140512-1299866.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=12 May 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Yoshida started all three matches despite facing competitions from the centre\u2013back and subsequently, Japan was eliminated from the tournament in the group stage, without winning any matches.<ref>{{cite news|script-title=ja:\u65e5\u672c\u3000\u30b3\u30fc\u30c8\u30b8\u30dc\u30ef\u30fc\u30eb\u306b\u9006\u8ee2\u8ca0\u3051\u3067\u9ed2\u661f\u767a\u9032\u2026\u672c\u7530\u5148\u5236\u5f3e\u3082\u5b9f\u3089\u305a|url=https://www.sponichi.co.jp/soccer/news/2014/06/15/kiji/K20140615008370750.html|publisher=Sponichi Annex|language=Japanese|date=15 June 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u5ca1\u5d0e\u540c\u70b9\u30d8\u30c3\u30c9\u30821-4\u5b8c\u6557\u2026\u65e5\u672c\u306fC\u7d44\u6700\u4e0b\u4f4d\u3067\u6557\u9000|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?141850-141850-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=25 June 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u71be\u70c8\u306aCB\u4e89\u3044\u306b\u3082\u5409\u7530\u300c\u7af6\u4e89\u306f\u30a6\u30a7\u30eb\u30ab\u30e0\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?140287-140287-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=5 June 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u6700\u5f8c\u307e\u3067\u7af6\u4e89\u3092\u4fc3\u3059\u30b6\u30c3\u30af\u300c\u30ec\u30ae\u30e5\u30e9\u30fc\u3092\u6c7a\u3081\u308b\u306e\u306f\u96e3\u3057\u3044\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?140345-140345-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=6 June 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Yoshida is first choice|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/11052965.yoshida-is-first-choice/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=5 March 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Despite this, He kept a clean sheet in a 0\u20130 draw against [[Greece national football team|Greece]] on 20 June 2014.<ref>{{cite news|script-title=ja:\u30b5\u30dd\u30fc\u30bf\u30fc\u3082\u898b\u653e\u3057\u305f\uff01\uff1f\u30b6\u30c3\u30af\u91c7\u914d\u306b\u53b3\u3057\u3059\u304e\u308b\u63a1\u70b9\u3000\u66f4\u8fed\u8ad6\u3082|url=https://www.sponichi.co.jp/soccer/news/2014/06/22/kiji/K20140622008417530.html|publisher=Sponichi Annex|language=Japanese|date=22 June 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Later in 2014, Yoshida scored his first Japan\u2019s goal in three years, as they beat [[Honduras national football team|Honduras]] 6\u20130 on 14 November 2014.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9060\u85e4\u5fa9\u5e30\u5f3e\u306a\u3069\u30a2\u30ae\u30fc\u30ecJ\u304c6\u767a\u5927\u52dd!!\u4e7e\u3001\u8c4a\u7530\u3082\u4ee3\u8868\u521d\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?151576-151576-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=14 November 2014|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2014, Yoshida was selected as a member of the Japanese team for the [[2015 AFC Asian Cup]] in Australia.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u676f\u30e1\u30f3\u30d0\u30fc23\u4eba\u304c\u6c7a\u5b9a!!\u6e05\u6b66\u304cW\u676f\u4ee5\u6765\u306e\u5fa9\u5e30\u3067\u30a2\u30ae\u30fc\u30ecJ\u521d\u62db\u96c6|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?153584-153584-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=15 December 2014|accessdate=23 August 2018}}</ref> He played Japan's opener match against debutant [[Palestine national football team|Palestine]] and scored the final goal in a 4\u20130 win.<ref>{{cite news|script-title=ja:\u9060\u85e4\u306e\u5148\u5236\u30df\u30c9\u30eb\u3067\u5e55\u958b\u3051!!\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u676f\u9023\u8987\u30784\u767a\u767a\u9032|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?155433-155433-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=12 January 2015|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Yoshida helped Japan kept two more clean sheets to advance through to the quarter\u2013finals.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u672c\u7530\u30012\u6226\u9023\u7d9aPK\u5f3e!!\u65e5\u672c\u306f\u30a4\u30e9\u30af\u30921-0\u3067\u4e0b\u30572\u9023\u52dd|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?155709-155709-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=16 January 2015|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|script-title=ja:\u672c\u75303\u6226\u9023\u767a!\u9999\u5ddd9\u6226\u3076\u308a\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb!\u65e5\u672c\u306f3\u9023\u52dd\u3067\u9996\u4f4d\u7a81\u7834|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?155930-155930-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=20 January 2015|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> However, he conceded a goal from [[Ali Mabkhout]] before Japan equalised and the match was played throughout 120 minutes; ultimately, they were eliminated after losing in penalty\u2013shootout.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5ddd\u5cf6\u3001PK\u3092\u6b62\u3081\u3089\u308c\u305a\u2026\u300c\u81ea\u5206\u81ea\u8eab\u3001\u529b\u4e0d\u8db3\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?156102-156102-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=23 January 2015|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> After the match, Yoshida acknowledged his fault for conceding a goal from the opposition team.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u75db\u6068\u306e\u4eca\u5927\u4f1a\u521d\u5931\u70b9\u2026\u9ebb\u4e5f\u300c\u5931\u70b9\u306f\u50d5\u306e\u30df\u30b9\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?156103-156103-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=23 January 2015|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nThroughout Japan\u2019s matches in the World Cup Qualifying Round, Yoshida then scored again in a 3\u20130 win against [[Cambodia national football team|Cambodia]] on 3 September 2015.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u683c\u4e0b\u30ab\u30f3\u30dc\u30b8\u30a2\u306b\u7269\u8db3\u308a\u306a\u30443-0\u3001\u672c\u7530&\u9ebb\u4e5f\u306e\u30df\u30c9\u30eb\u5f3e\u306b\u9999\u5ddd\u304c\u30cf\u30ea\u30ebJ\u521d\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?171109-171109-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=3 September 2015|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> He later helped Japan keep two more clean sheets against [[Afghanistan national football team|Afghanistan]] and [[Syria national football team|Syria]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u30cf\u30ea\u30ebJ\u3001\u201c\u30a2\u30a6\u30a7\u30fc\u201d\u3067\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u30e9\u30c3\u30b7\u30e5!! \u9999\u5ddd&\u5ca1\u5d0e\u304c2\u5f97\u70b9\u30676\u767a\u5feb\u52dd|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?171456-171456-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=8 September 2015|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u65e5\u672c\uff25\u7d44\u9996\u4f4d\uff01\uff13\u5f97\u70b9\u30b7\u30ea\u30a2\u6483\u7834\uff0f\uff37\u676f\uff12\u6b21\u4e88\u9078\u8a73\u7d30|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/1550010.html |publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=8 October 2015|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Yoshida kept four more clean sheets in the World Cup Qualifying Round between 12 November 2015 and 29 March 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u672c\u7530\u304cW\u676f\u4e88\u90785\u6226\u9023\u767a\u3082\u2026\u5927\u82e6\u6226\u306e\u30cf\u30ea\u30ebJ\u3001\u683c\u4e0b\u30ab\u30f3\u30dc\u30b8\u30a2\u306b\u8f9b\u52dd|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?176665-176665-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=12 November 2015|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title= 5\u767a\u5927\u52dd\u306e\u30cf\u30ea\u30ebJ\u30012\u6b21\u4e88\u9078\u51688\u8a66\u5408\u5b8c\u5c01\u3067\u9996\u4f4d\u901a\u904e|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?186147-186147-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=29 March 2016|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> During the run, he scored two goals against [[Singapore national football team|Singapore]] and Afghanistan.<ref>{{cite news|title=3\u767a\u52dd\u5229\u30675\u304b\u6708\u524d\u306e\u501f\u308a\u8fd4\u3059\u3082\u2026\u30cf\u30ea\u30eb\u300c\u3082\u3046\u5c11\u3057\u70b9\u3092\u53d6\u308c\u305f\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?176250-176250-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=12 November 2015|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> <ref>{{cite news|title=\u3010\u65e5\u672c \uff15-\uff10 \u30a2\u30d5\u30ac\u30cb\u30b9\u30bf\u30f3\u3011\u5ca1\u5d0e\u306e\u30d5\u30a1\u30a4\u30f3\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u3092\u76ae\u5207\u308a\u306b\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u30e9\u30c3\u30b7\u30e5\u3067\u5927\u52dd\uff01|url=https://www.soccerdigestweb.com/news/detail/id=14853|publisher=Soccer Digest Web|language=Japanese|date=24 March 2016|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Three months later on 3 June 2016, Yoshida scored a brace, scoring in the fourth and five goal, in a 7\u20132 win against [[Bulgaria national football team|Bulgaria]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u30cf\u30ea\u30eb\u65e5\u672c\u3001\u30d6\u30eb\u30ac\u30ea\u30a2\u306b\uff17\u767a\u5727\u52dd\uff0f\u30ad\u30ea\u30f3\u676f\u8a73\u7d30|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/1657223.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=3 June 2016|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> The following March, he captained Japan for the first time in his career and helped the national side beat United Arabs Emirates 2\u20130.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u300c\u9577\u8c37\u90e8\u3055\u3093\u304c\u3044\u306a\u304f\u3066\u8ca0\u3051\u305f\u3068\u8a00\u308f\u308c\u305f\u304f\u306a\u304b\u3063\u305f\u300d UAE\u306e\u524d\u306b\u7acb\u3061\u306f\u3060\u304b\u3063\u305f\u201c\u30ad\u30e3\u30d7\u30c6\u30f3\u201d\u9ebb\u4e5f|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?212093-212093-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=22 March 2017|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=23\u6b73\u4e45\u4fdd\u306eA\u4ee3\u8868\u521d\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u306b34\u6b73\u4eca\u91ce\u304c\u4ee3\u8868\u5fa9\u5e30\u5f3e!!\u30cf\u30ea\u30ebJ\u304cUAE\u306b\u30ea\u30d9\u30f3\u30b8\u679c\u305f\u30572\u4f4d\u30ad\u30fc\u30d7|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?212089-212089-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=24 March 2017|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> After the match, Yoshida said: \"I have played several times in my team, but it is a big thing to be the captain of the national team. I felt it.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=\u30ad\u30e3\u30d7\u30c6\u30f3\u30de\u30fc\u30af\u3092\u5dfb\u3044\u305f\u9ebb\u4e5f\u300c\u8a87\u308a\u306b\u306a\u308b1\u65e5\u3060\u3063\u305f\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?212107-212107-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=24 March 2017|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> In a follow\u2013up match against [[Thailand national football team|Thailand]], he scored again, in a 4\u20130 win.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u65e5\u672c\u30014\u767a\u5feb\u52dd\u3067W\u676f\u51fa\u5834\u3078\u524d\u9032\uff01\u3000\u9999\u5ddd\u3001\u5ca1\u5d0e\u3001\u4e45\u4fdd\u3001\u5409\u7530\u304c\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u2026\u5ddd\u5cf6\u306fPK\u963b\u6b62|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20170328/568484.html|publisher=Soccer King|language=Japanese|date=28 March 2017|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Three months later, on 31 August 2017, Yoshida started the whole match against Australia and helped Japan qualified for the World Cup after beating the Socceroos 2\u20130.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u65e5\u672c\uff16\u5927\u4f1a\u9023\u7d9a\uff37\u676f\uff01\u6d45\u91ce\uff36\u5f3e\uff0f\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u6700\u7d42\u4e88\u9078\u8a73\u7d30|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/1880295.html |publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=31 August 2017|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Qatar - Japan, AFC Asian Cup 2019 38.jpg|thumb|right|300px|Yoshida booked for handball during a match against [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]] in the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup Final|AFC Asian Cup final]]; leading to a penalty converted successfully from the opposition team and resulting Japan losing 3\u20131.]]\n\nOn 31 May 2018, Yoshida was selected in the 23-man squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/sports/2018/05/31/soccer/nishino-reveals-23-man-squad-world-cup|title=Nishino reveals 23-man squad for World Cup|publisher=The Japan Times|accessdate=7 July 2018}}</ref> It was expected once again that Yoshida will be starting in the centre\u2013back position ahead of the tournament.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u65b0\u30b7\u30b9\u30c6\u30e0\u306e\u624b\u5fdc\u3048\u306f!? \u9ebb\u4e5f\u300c\u8a66\u5408\u3092\u3084\u3063\u3066\u307f\u306a\u3044\u3068\u5206\u304b\u3089\u306a\u3044\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?245914-245914-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=29 May 2018|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<be>{{cite news|title=\u7c73\u30e1\u30c7\u30a3\u30a2\u304c\u30ed\u30b7\u30a2W\u676f\u3078\u81e8\u3080\u65e5\u672c\u4ee3\u8868\u3092\u89e3\u8aac\u2026\u653b\u6483\u9663\u306e\u8981\u306f\u672c\u7530\u572d\u4f51? |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?243639-243639-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=2 May 2018|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u30d9\u30eb\u30ae\u30fc\u30e1\u30c7\u30a3\u30a2\u304c\u30d9\u30b9\u30c816\u3067\u5bfe\u6226\u306e\u897f\u91ce\u30b8\u30e3\u30d1\u30f3\u3092\u5206\u6790\u300c\u6211\u3005\u3092\u7aae\u5730\u306b\u8ffd\u3044\u8fbc\u3080\u53ef\u80fd\u6027\u304c\u3042\u308b\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?248562-248562-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=30 June 2018|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> He played every single minute in all the group stage matches against [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]],<ref>{{cite web|last1=Jennings|first1=Patrick|title=Colombia 1 Japan 2|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44439048|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=7 July 2018|location=Saransk|date=19 June 2018}}</ref> [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Johnston|first1=Neil|title=Japan 2 Senegal 2|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44439190|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=7 July 2018|location=Ekaterinburg|date=24 June 2018}}</ref> and [[Poland national football team|Poland]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Hafez|first1=Shamoon|title=Japan 0 Poland 1|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44439298|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=7 July 2018|location=Volgograd|date=28 June 2018}}</ref> His side were knocked out of the tournament after losing 3\u20132 to [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] in the round of 16 match.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Begley|first1=Emlyn|title=Belgium 3 Japan 2|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44597759|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=7 July 2018|location=Rostov-on-Don|date=2 July 2018}}</ref> His performance in the World Cup earned praises from the British media, such as, [[The Guardian]] and [[BBC Sport]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5409\u7530\u9ebb\u4e5f\u306e\u540d\u524d\u3082\u2026\u82f1\u7d19\u304c\u3053\u3053\u307e\u3067\u306e\u30ed\u30b7\u30a2W\u676f\u30d9\u30b9\u30c8\u30a4\u30ec\u30d6\u30f3\u3092\u9078\u51fa|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?248211-248211-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=26 June 2018|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u5409\u7530\u9ebb\u4e5f\u304c\u6700\u9ad8\u70b9\u7372\u5f97\u3067\u82f1\u30e1\u30c7\u30a3\u30a2\u306eMOM\u306b!\u30eb\u30ab\u30af\u309290\u5206\u9593\u6291\u3048\u305f\u3053\u3068\u3092\u8a55\u4fa1|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?248864-248864-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=3 July 2018|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2018, Yoshida was one of 23 Japanese players selected for the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=SAMURAI BLUE (Japan National Team) Squad, Schedule - AFC Asian Cup UAE 2019 (1/5-2/1)|url=http://www.jfa.jp/eng/news/00019975/|date=13 December 2018|website=jfa.jp|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Ahead of the tournament, he was given the captaincy once again.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u82e5\u624b\u306b\u306e\u3057\u304b\u304b\u308b\u671f\u5f85\u2026\u9ebb\u4e5f\u306f\u30d7\u30ec\u30c3\u30b7\u30e3\u30fc\u3092\u6b53\u8fce\u300c\u6226\u3048\u306a\u3044\u3068\u3084\u3063\u3066\u3044\u3051\u306a\u3044\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?263682-263682-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=8 January 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Yoshida started the tournament as captain well when he helped Japan win 3\u20132 against [[Turkmenistan national football team|Turkmenistan]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u65e5\u672c\u5927\u8feb\uff12\u767a\u3001\u5802\u5b89\u5f3e\u3067\u30d2\u30e4\u30d2\u30e4\u52dd\u5229\uff0f\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u676f\u8a73\u7d30|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201901080001324.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=10 January 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> In a follow\u2013up match against [[Oman national football team|Oman]], Yoshida led the side to keep a clean sheet, in a 1\u20130 win to advance to the knockout stage.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u65e5\u672c\u4ee3\u8868\u30012\u9023\u52dd\u3067\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u676f\u6c7a\u52ddT\u9032\u51fa\uff01\u3000\u539f\u53e3\u306ePK\u5f3e\u3067\u30aa\u30de\u30fc\u30f3\u3092\u4e0b\u3059|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20190114/891839.html|publisher=Soccer King|language=Japanese|date=14 January 2011|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> He later helped Japan kept three clean sheets that led the national side reaching the final for the first time since 2011.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u65e5\u672c\uff18\u5f37\uff01\u51a8\u5b89\uff36\u5f3e\u30b5\u30a6\u30b8\u4e0b\u3059\uff0f\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u676f\u6c7a\u52dd\uff34\u8a73\u7d30|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201901210000391.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=21 January 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u65e5\u672c\u4ee3\u8868\u3001\u5802\u5b89\u306e\u201cVAR\u5f3e\u201d\u3067\u30d9\u30b9\u30c84\u9032\u51fa\uff01\u3000FIFA\u30e9\u30f3\u30af100\u4f4d\u306e\u30d9\u30c8\u30ca\u30e0\u306b\u8f9b\u304f\u3082\u52dd\u5229|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20190124/897439.html|publisher=Soccer King|language=Japanese|date=24 January 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u5927\u8feb\uff12\u767a\u3060\uff01\u539f\u53e3\uff11\u767a\u3060\uff01\u65e5\u672c\uff13\u767a\u6c7a\u52dd\u3000\u30a4\u30e9\u30f3\u6483\u7834|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201901290000012.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=29 January 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> In the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup Final|AFC Asian Cup final]] against Qatar, Yoshida started and captained the side, as they lost 3\u20131, finishing as runner\u2013up in the process.<ref>{{cite news|script-title=ja:\u82e6\u3057\u307f\u629c\u3044\u305f\u5357\u91ce\u304c\u4e00\u77e2\u3001\u5c0f\uff13\u304b\u3089\u5909\u308f\u3089\u306c\u5f37\u3044\u4f53\u5e79|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201902020000084.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=ja|date=2 February 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> During the match, he was penalised for handball, leading Qatar to successfully convert the penalty to give the opposition team a 3\u20131 lead.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5409\u7530\u9ebb\u4e5f\u306e\u30cf\u30f3\u30c9\u3067\u306ePK\u5224\u5b9a\u306b\u6d77\u5916\u6709\u529b\u30e1\u30c7\u30a3\u30a2\u3082\u540c\u60c5 \u300c\u3053\u308c\u307e\u3067\u898b\u305f\u4e2d\u3067\u6700\u3082\u30d0\u30ab\u3052\u305fPK\u306e\u4e00\u3064\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?265459-265459-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=2 February 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> After the match, Yoshida said: \"I felt that the team had a good performance in the (semi-final) match against Iran, and they felt that they were going to be able to go this way and be able to go this way. I couldn't control, and I didn't win. I feel unhappy.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=\u6094\u6068\u306e\u30ad\u30e3\u30d7\u30c6\u30f3\u2026\u9ebb\u4e5f\u300c\u30c1\u30fc\u30e0\u306e\u6cb9\u65ad\u3084\u9699\u3092\u5f8b\u3059\u308b\u3053\u3068\u304c\u3067\u304d\u305a\u4e0d\u7532\u6590\u306a\u3044\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?265399-265399-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=2 February 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> However, Yoshida\u2019s call-up to the tournament caused new manager [[Ralph Hasenh\u00fcttl]] having selection problem during his absent.<ref>{{cite news|title=Southampton boss Ralph Hasenhuttl discusses Maya Yoshida|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/17417412.southampton-boss-ralph-hasenhuttl-discusses-maya-yoshida/|publisher=DSouthern Daily Echo|date=8 February 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> In response, he acknowledged the risk he took by playing for Japan in the AFC Asian Cup.<ref>{{cite news|title=Southampton defender Maya Yoshida is itching to play again|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/17461314.southampton-defender-maya-yoshida-is-itching-to-play-again/|publisher=Southern Daily Echo|date=27 February 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the conclusion of the AFC Asian Cup, Yoshida didn\u2019t receive a call\u2013up from Japan until August.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u4e45\u4fdd\u5efa\u82f1\u304c\u30ab\u30bf\u30fc\u30ebW\u676f\u4e88\u9078\u3078!! \u9ebb\u4e5f\u3001\u9060\u85e4\u304c\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u676f\u4ee5\u6765\u306eA\u4ee3\u8868\u5fa9\u5e30|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?283518-283518-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=30 August 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> He was also given the captaincy.<ref>{{cite news|title=7\u304b\u6708\u3076\u308a\u5fa9\u5e30\u306e\u30ad\u30e3\u30d7\u30c6\u30f3\u9ebb\u4e5f\u306b\u7d76\u5bfe\u306e\u4fe1\u983c\u3001\u68ee\u4fdd\u76e3\u7763\u300c\u5fc3\u914d\u3057\u3066\u306a\u3044\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?283893-283893-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=2 September 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> Yoshida captained the remaining matches of 2019 with clean sheets.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u68ee\u4fdd\u30b8\u30e3\u30d1\u30f3\u304c\u5f37\u8c6a\u30d1\u30e9\u30b0\u30a2\u30a4\u3092\u7834\u308b\uff0f\u30b9\u30b3\u30a2\u8a73\u7d30|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201909040000723.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=4 September 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u65e5\u672c\u304c\u30df\u30e3\u30f3\u30de\u30fc\u306b\u5feb\u52dd\uff01\u3000\u30ab\u30bf\u30fc\u30ebW\u676f\u3078\u597d\u767a\u9032\u2026\u4e45\u4fdd\u306f\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u4e88\u9078\u6700\u5e74\u5c11\u51fa\u5834\u8a18\u9332\u3092\u66f4\u65b0|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20190910/978162.html|publisher=Soccer King|language=Japanese|date=10 September 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u65e5\u672c\uff13\u767a\u5feb\u52dd\uff01\u5357\u91ce\uff12\u767a\uff06\u6d45\u91ce\u5f3e\uff0f\uff37\u676f\uff12\u6b21\u4e88\u9078\u8a73\u7d30|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201910150000027.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=15 October 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> During this run, he scored his first Japan\u2019s goal of the year, in a 6\u20130 win against [[Mongolia national football team|Mongolia]] on 10 October 2019.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u68ee\u4fdd\u65e5\u672c\uff16\u767a\u5feb\u52dd\u3001\u30e2\u30f3\u30b4\u30eb\u6483\u7834\uff0f\uff37\u676f\uff12\u6b21\u4e88\u9078\u8a73\u7d30|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201910100000497.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=10 October 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref> On 14 November 2019, Yoshida also played his 100th match for Japan against [[Kyrgyzstan national football team|Kyrgyzstan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/18029630.southampton-defender-maya-yoshida-closes-landmark-moment/|title=Southampton defender Maya Yoshida closes in on landmark moment|website=Southern Daily Echo|date=12 November 2019}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u65e5\u672c\u5357\u91ce\u5f3e\u306a\u3069\uff12\u767a\u3067\u5b8c\u5c01\u52dd\u5229\uff0f\uff37\u676f\uff12\u6b21\u4e88\u9078\u8a73\u7d30|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201911140000536.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=14 November 2019|accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|4 January 2020}}<ref>[http://aus.worldfootball.net/spieler_profil/maya-yoshida/2/ Maya Yoshida : Record worldfootball.net]</ref><ref name=\"SW\" />\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!rowspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup<sup>[[#notes gs1|1]]</sup>\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup<sup>[[#notes gs2|2]]</sup>\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental<sup>[[#notes gs3|3]]</sup>\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other<sup>[[#notes gs4|4]]</sup>\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Nagoya Grampus]]\n|[[2007 J. League Division 1|2007]]\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[J1 League|J. League Division 1]]\n|19||0||2||1||3||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||24||1\n|-\n|[[2008 J. League Division 1|2008]]\n|22||1||3||1||4||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||29||2\n|-\n|[[2009 J. League Division 1|2009]]\n|30||4||6||1||1||1||11||2||colspan=\"2\"|-||48||8\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!71||5||11||3||8||1||11||2||colspan=\"2\"|-||101||11\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[VVV-Venlo]]\n|[[2009\u201310 Eredivisie|2009\u201310]]\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Eredivisie]]\n|0||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||0||0\n|-\n|[[2010\u201311 Eredivisie|2010\u201311]]\n|20||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||4||0||24||0\n|-\n|[[2011\u201312 Eredivisie|2011\u201312]]\n|32||5||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||4||0||37||5\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 Eredivisie|2012\u201313]]\n|2||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||2||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!54||5||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||8||0||63||5\n|-\n|rowspan=\"9\"|[[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]]\n|[[2012\u201313 Southampton F.C. season|2012\u201313]]<ref>{{soccerbase season|57517|2012|accessdate=27 February 2017}}</ref>\n|rowspan=\"8\"|[[Premier League]]\n|32||0||1||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||34||0\n|-\n|[[2013\u201314 Southampton F.C. season|2013\u201314]]<ref>{{soccerbase season|57517|2013|accessdate=27 February 2017}}</ref>\n|8||1||3||0||3||1||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||14||2\n|-\n|[[2014\u201315 Southampton F.C. season|2014\u201315]]<ref>{{soccerbase season|57517|2014|accessdate=27 February 2017}}</ref>\n|22||1||colspan=\"2\"|-||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||23||1\n|-\n|[[2015\u201316 Southampton F.C. season|2015\u201316]]<ref>{{soccerbase season|57517|2015|accessdate=27 February 2017}}</ref>\n|20||1||1||0||2||1||4||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||27||2\n|-\n|[[2016\u201317 Southampton F.C. season|2016\u201317]]<ref>{{soccerbase season|57517|2016|accessdate=19 March 2017}}</ref>\n|23||1||2||1||6||0||6||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||37||2\n|-\n|[[2017\u201318 Southampton F.C. season|2017\u201318]]<ref>{{soccerbase season|57517|2017|accessdate=14 May 2018}}</ref>\n|24||2||3||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||28||2\n|-\n|[[2018\u201319 Southampton F.C. season|2018\u201319]]<ref>{{soccerbase season|57517|2018|accessdate=5 April 2019}}</ref>\n|17||0||0||0||3||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||20||0\n|-\n|[[2019\u201320 Southampton F.C. season|2019\u201320]]<ref>{{soccerbase season|57517|2019|accessdate=1 February 2020}}</ref>\n|8||0||1||0||2||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||11||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!154||6||11||1||19||2||10||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||194||9\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career total\n!279||16||23||4||27||3||21||2||8||0||358||25\n|}\n<div id=\"notes gs1\"></div><sup>1</sup><small>Includes [[Emperor's Cup]], [[KNVB Cup]] and [[FA Cup]].</small>\n<div id=\"notes gs2\"></div><sup>2</sup><small>Includes [[J. League Cup]] and [[Football League Cup]].</small>\n<div id=\"notes gs3\"></div><sup>3</sup><small>Includes [[AFC